{"name":"Porter's Wynd #1","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.vPPvQKEcGUqeoJvi"},"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A well-to-do house, with two ground-floor rooms, and a small garret sleeping area; it is home to &lt;BLANK&gt;.</p>","_id":"04Damtjb5Jkm2v8K"}
{"name":"Metzener's Butchers","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>@Actor[Rosalin Metzener]'s grandparents came to Halberst just over 50 years ago and set up Metzener's Butchers.&nbsp; It very quickly became the most popular butchers in town, and just over 10 years it became the only butchers in town; but that hasn't resulted in a drop of quality.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The farms around Halberst raise mainly sheep and pigs, so Metzener's primarily deal in Pork and Lamb / Mutton.&nbsp; However, they also deal with Beef and Goose.&nbsp; They are particularly well known for thier Juniper Brined Gammons, Salt-Aged Beef, and Snoked Sage Sausage.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The ground floor is given over to the butchery, with meats being shipped in from Schlacter's Abbatoir &amp; Tannery outside the North Gate of town.&nbsp; The upper floor is the dwelling for the Metzener family.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"1l8R0mrLYjTsjGKY"}
{"name":"House Kniehocher","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dqjx1ld0k6u","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/02: Noble & Trade Houses","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>For over twenty years House Kniehocher has been absent from Halberst, after a misunderstanding with the previous Reeve saw them withdraw to their Country Estate just South-West of Ruhmpunkt; with their holdings on @JournalEntry[Trader's Row] sitting empty and become dilapidated, and their Townhouse on @JournalEntry[Kennel Lane] being mothballed, recieving only one or two annual visits from hosehold staff to keep things in order.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>With recent investment in their Trader's Row holding being forthcoming from the @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall], which had to be matched by the House, they have decided to re-establish a permanent presence in Halberst.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Actor[Heidrun Kniehocher] has been sent to represent the House in Halberst.&nbsp; She has travlled with a small household staff of 5 people; a cook, two housemaids, a clerk, and a bodyguard.&nbsp; She has also travelled with a Master Tanner, @Actor[Griswold Erchenmeker], to take over the running of the Halberst @JournalEntry[Kniehocher Tannery]{Tannery}, that the House has recently took an active role in, with a view to expanding the House's standing and wealth in Halberst.</p>","img":"","_id":"203dv1cClsMKXGVk"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_785h5s8h1e9","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/08: Religion","color":"#000000","name":"08: Religion","children":["7hQBonM4F0OIOnOP","vLAmP3ldzWVNxUBm","qnCppuDWpk3Me2dV"],"folderPath":["temp_syvf2bs7n7"]}},"content":"","_id":"20cbyKJ0z1GFVEjS"}
{"name":"<BLANK> Warehouse","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A large, two-storey warehouse situated where @JournalEntry[Guild Street] meets @JournalEntry[Beggar's Rise].&nbsp; With a small cobbled yard out the front and two low tables for produce.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The warehouse is currently used by @Actor&lt;BLANK&gt;, selling &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>","_id":"29pZHvPwKumFraRe"}
{"name":"Kennel Lane","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Connecting the West end of the @JournalEntry[Karstadt Road] with @JournalEntry[Beggar's Rise] is Dog Street, named such because when a generation or so ago the then Reeve of Halberst, Hertil Heidorfer, was a renowned Huntsman he ensconced his Kennel-Master on the street.&nbsp; Although Heidorfer and his Kennel-Master are barely remembered now the street name lingers on.&nbsp;</p>","_id":"3NQhKliGYLT7ZtGq"}
{"name":"Baker's Row","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Baker's Row runs parallel to the river from Threeways along to Lenkster's Court.&nbsp; The @JournalEntry[River Reaver Inn], The @JournalEntry[Fisherman's Guild], @JournalEntry[Brotbacker's Bakery] and @JournalEntry[Morrslieb's Marsh] are all on Baker's Row.</p>","img":"","_id":"3YnkmWY1iYSx4jIO"}
{"name":"Krugelmann's Lane","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Opposite @JournalEntry[Temple Street #1] is small alley that leads to the back of @JournalEntry[Hardtstein's Hardware], to one side of the alley is @JournalEntry[Karstadt Road #3] and to the other is @JournalEntry[Krugelmann's Folly Hostel].</p>","_id":"3oZgBXZhMqHezQXi"}
{"name":"Honourable Fellowship of Merchants & Traders","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Honourable Fellowship of Merchants &amp; Traders has a small office in the @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall].&nbsp; It really is only used for record keeping though, as the Guild has too many Members for the room to be used for meetings.&nbsp; In fact the Guild has&nbsp; amajor issue, in that almost all areas of Trade and Commerce have demanded their own Sub-Committe, leading to the ludicrous situation where there are now at least 12 such sub-committees, each with only one or two members.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The current Chairman, @Actor[Johnas Kurschner], is keen to maintain this disorganised chaos, as it means there is never enough agreement among the Membership to nominate a new Chairman, meaning that - according to the Guild Charter - with no clear new candidate the current Chairman continues unopposed for another year.&nbsp; Johnas has managed to mainitain his Chairmanship for the last 4 years because of this process.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"4ChniG9Q2ylM0cZ7"}
{"name":"Grumbling Griffon Tavern","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pxh26pbtbf","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/06: Taverns & Inns","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><strong>Sign: </strong>An angry looking Griffon.</p>\n<p><strong>Proprietor:</strong> @Actor[Isolde Kuhrenwald]</p>\n<p><strong>Staff: </strong>@Actor[Inga Kuhrenwald]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Griffon is noted for its eclectic collection of tankards, gathered from all over the Old World.&nbsp; Anyone who presents Isolde Kuhrenwald with a unique tankard, wooden or metallic, will be treated to an evening of free drinks.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Griffon became the Grumbling Griffon when it became the regular for Townsmen and Clerks employed at the Town Hall.</span></p>","img":"","_id":"5DP17ivxvcIUGRZu"}
{"name":"Kellner's Boarding House","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Situated on @JournalEntry[Lenkster's Court (West View)], between @JournalEntry[Baker's Row #1 &amp; 2] and @JournalEntry[Lenkster's Court #1 - 3] is Kellner's Boarding House.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The building has a two-story section, and a three-storey section and was, once upon a time, the Town House of the now disolved House von Edelstein-Herzog, which pased into obscurity almost 50 years ago having no heir, and having forfeited its lands to @JournalEntry[Graf Steirlich von Bruner]'s father. The building sat dormant, slowly falling into disrepair until leased from the Graf Steirlich von Bruner just over 20 years ago.&nbsp; Shortly after the lease was signed the @JournalEntry[Estimable Guild of Craftsmen] were commissioned to renovate the building, a process that took a whole Spring and Summer.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Once the renovations were complete the building was registered at the @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall] as Kellner's Boarding House, and a Housekeeper, @Actor[Abighild Kretschner], was listed as the proprietor. Abighild uses the small two-story section as her own dwelling, and makes a little extra money for her employers by hosting a Market Stall outside the building.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The three-storey section contains, on the ground floor, a Kitchen and Dining Room area, guests are afforded breakfast, and may pay extra for an evening meal. The 1st and 2nd floors have the same layout, a staircase, and 4 Single Rooms, each room contains a Bed, a Chest or Drawers, a Bedside Table, and a chamber-pot.&nbsp;Each rooms can be booked out in packages of 10 Days, to include Breakfast, for the price of 8/6d.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Kellner's is a chain of Boarding Houses, with premisies in Halberst, Siedlung, and Neumarkt; the business is owned by Fabian Stubenmeister, and minor functionary of @JournalEntry[Barony of Bohrn]{House Bohrn}.</p>\n</section>\n<p><strong>1st Floor</strong></p>\n<p>Room 1:&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Room 2:</p>\n<p>Room 3:</p>\n<p>Room 4:</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>2nd Floor</strong></p>\n<p>Room 5:</p>\n<p>Room 6:</p>\n<p>Room 7:</p>\n<p>Room 8:</p>\n<hr />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"5mav4opOu0HUfxck"}
{"name":"Breton's Corner","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>At the end of @JournalEntry[Lenkster's Row] is a small set of steps leading up the side of @JournalEntry[Dankov Lenkster's Shack] to the rear of the @JournalEntry[Wandering Bretonian Inn].&nbsp; Known locally as Breton's Corner this area is favourite spot for local youth to sit and drink, and for older youths to court.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The grass covered bank that is behind the Wndering Bretonian and drops down on to @JournalEntry[Lenkster's Row] is filled with wild herbs, including Wild Garlic, Thyme, Sage and Rosemary.</p>","img":"worlds/uber-chron/images/Halberst/Hal_Breton%27s_Corner.png","_id":"5pcqQwrYIRPLrp3X"}
{"name":"Wurtzmenger's Spice Emporium","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Halberst is one of three outlets for Wurtzmenger's Spice Emporium, owned by Wurtzmenger &amp; Sons of Ubersreik; the other two outlets are in Ubersreik and Siedlung.&nbsp; In Halberst the Emporium is operated by @Actor[Hans Stahler-Gander], he managed the Emporium for 7 years, and is a Member (IGS) of the @JournalEntry[Honourable Fellowship of Merchants &amp; Traders].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Tasse = measure of spices, roughly 1/4 pint.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"6TaZDUQbl9YIlgRp"}
{"name":"Wandering Bretonian Inn","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pxh26pbtbf","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/06: Taverns & Inns","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><strong>Sign: </strong>A Man in Bretonian clothing carring a stick over his shoulder.</p>\n<p><strong>Proprietor:</strong> @Actor[Solange Aubergiere]</p>\n<p><strong>Staff:</strong> &lt;TO SORT&gt;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">Part of a growing chain of Inns in the region owned by @JournalEntry[Imperial Expressways] The Wandering Bretonian is the Coaching Inn for Halberst.&nbsp; It has stabling for upto 8 horses (as a Coaching Inn it is the only place in Halberst allowed to stable horses within the town-walls), 4 private, double rooms, 6 quad-rooms, and a common bunk-room capable of sleeping 12 people.&nbsp; The food is reasonable quality, but a little pricey, as are the rooms; but as it is the only Coaching Inn in town it has a monopoly on that customer base.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0798%; height: 160px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\" colspan=\"3\"><strong>The Wandering Bretonian</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Lodgings &amp; Services</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Meals</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Drinks</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Bunkroom Bed: 10d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Porridge / Gruel: 4d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Standard Ale: 3d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Quad Room: 4/- each&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Private Room: 10/-&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Bread, Fruit &amp; Cheese: 1/-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Spirits 1/4 Pint: 10d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Hot Bath: 6d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Roast Platter: 2/5d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Wine, Bottle, Cheap: 1/3d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Clothes Service: 2d per item</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Roast Plum Duck: 2/8d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Bretonian Brandy: 16d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Cherry Clafoutis: 14d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Calvadoz: 16d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Stabling, per Horse: 10d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"6Yn0Fb7Ay5BjsKac"}
{"name":"Guild Street #1&2","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.Z4yOmOJLGnlyRgrO"},"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A two-storey building; each floor is a separate dwelling.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Ground Floor: &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>First Floor: &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>","_id":"71aDgtRSkt96v3Ex"}
{"name":"Brotbacker's Bakery","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Next door to the @JournalENtry[River Reaver Inn] and sitting opposite the @JournalEntry[Fisherman's Guild] is Bratbacker's Bakery.&nbsp; A three-storey building that is always surrounded by the smell of Bread and Beer.&nbsp; @Actor[Tobias Bachmann] runs the bakery, ably assisted by his brother @Actor[Henryk Bachmann] and Henryk's wife, @Actor[Marianna Bachmann]{Marianna} and their 13 year old daughter @Actor[Adelyn Bachmann]{Adelyn}.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The oven sits on the ground floor, with the second floor taken up by preparations and storage areas, and the smaller third floor, has a dwelling shared by the whole family, though Tobias often sleep sin the bakery as he tends the oven, which should never go out, and the newly formed venture of brewing (that takes up half of the ground floor) @Item[Reaver's Bite (Pint)] in collaboration with @Actor[Sigrid Krugmann].</p>","img":"","_id":"7Lf0X5xvXtV18QXh"}
{"name":"Priest's House","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_785h5s8h1e9","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/08: Religion","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A two-storey house, with an overhanging upper floor.&nbsp; This is the home of the Clerics based at the @JournalEntry[Temple of Sigmar].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The head priest has a private room, and there is a small bunkroom for the reamaining clergy, capable of sleepng 4 in two doouble-bunks.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The building is well maintained and in better condition than many of the buildings in Halberst.</p>","_id":"7hQBonM4F0OIOnOP"}
{"name":"Fisherman's Guild","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_56jqb4pyr6l","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/05: River Front","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Fisherman's Guild contains a private bar for Members In Good Standing of the Guild and their registered guests.&nbsp; It also has 4 Single Rooms for use by Members, currently two are in use; one by the Guild Housekeeper @Actor[Nobilius \"Nobby\" Buttermann], and the other by @Actor[Xander Senker], a local fisherman who has resided in the Guildhouse for almost 7 years.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Guildmaster is locally renowned fishwife @Actor[Ursula Schieringer], she has been Guildmaster for 3 years, and by tradition can only serve for four.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The lower dock-level of the Guildhouse is used for landing smaller catches, or prize-catches.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>","_id":"843afJWCFgAQpzmU"}
{"name":"Lenkster's Court #1 - 3","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A long two-storey building, with the ground-floor taken up by a common-room and kitchen area.&nbsp; This area is shared by the three families who each use one of the bedrooms upstairs.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Each bedroom has a double bed and a wardrobe, and behind a small room-divider a double bunk-bed for the children.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The families that liver here are:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1) &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>\n<p>2) &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>\n<p>3) &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>","_id":"9IqpLiYjbjJde3Gm"}
{"name":"Doing The Round","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qgqh4rei9ki","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/08: Special Events","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>An infamous drinking challenge among the ne-er-do-wells of Halberst, \"Doing The Round\" involves drinking one standard measure of every alcoholic drink that the Twelve Daggers serves.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Anyone doing so gets their money back, which is a considerable sum of money (<span style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Cost of \"Doing The Round\": 2GC 2/11d</em>) and gets their name added to the \"Roll of Honour\".</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">See @JournalEntry[Consume Alcohol Modifications] to roleplay this event.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"9Xk6mu5h6UJNq8y6"}
{"name":"Lenkster's Court (West View)","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Mid way along its length, just past Morrslieb's Marsh, Baker's Row broadens out to almost form a natural courtyard, bounded on the West side by @JournalEntry[Kellner's Boarding House] and...</p>","_id":"Ar8On4ESemgUDaRk"}
{"name":"Grauwerk Road","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Heading roughly North from Coachman's Corner and taken up almost entirely by the @JournalEntry[Wandering Bretonian Inn] and its out-buildings is Grauwerk Road.&nbsp; The only Coach Route through the town, coaches pass through heading South to @JournalEntry[Gottheim] and onward to @JournalEntry[Buchendorf] and @JournalEntry[Ubersreik].&nbsp; Depending on the weather a coach can be expected through Halberst every two to four days.</p>","img":"worlds/uber-chron/images/Halberst/Hal_Wandering_Bretonian.png","_id":"AxlUwrzx1vT47EJ8"}
{"name":"Kurschner's Furs","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>@Actor[Johnas Kurschner] has worked with Fur since he was old enough to walk, learning the trade at the knee of first his Grandfather and then his Mother.&nbsp; Working closely with @Actor[Rosamunde Gerber] at the @JournalEntry[Kniehocher Tannery] to the North of town, he ensures his business has access to the very best Fur the Duchies of @JournalEntry[Duchy of Karstadt]{Karstadt} and @JournalEntry[Duchy of Grauwerk]{Grauwerk} have to offer.</p>","_id":"CIwpPt4tWYfnYq2f"}
{"name":"House Landervogt","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dqjx1ld0k6u","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/02: Noble & Trade Houses","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>House Landervogt, formally House Landervogt von Reikherz, started out as a small Merchant House, they streadily grew into a large Merchant House and was, 35 years ago, raised to the nobility by @Actor[Graf Steirlich von Bruner] for decades of loyal service to Halberst and the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Karstadt] and @JournalEntry[Duchy of Grauwerk].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>They have a Manor House and Estates at Reikherz, but effectively their seat of power is Halberst, wherein they own a large, three-story building, that dominates @JournalEntry[Upper Dock Street] although the building is not currently used by @Actor[Constanza Landervogt] as she is afforded use of the @JournalEntry[Reeve's House].&nbsp; A small cadre of servants maintains the house should it be needed to host visiting dignitaries, and indeed the house has hosted @Actor[Graf Steirlich von Bruner] on two previous occassions.&nbsp; Constanza's son, @Actor[Reinhart Landervogt] resides at Reikherz and manages the family's estate there, an estate that is in effect newly founded, having been without a leige-lord for almost a century.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"DNGTvtAVokUedCu7"}
{"name":"Trader's End","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>At the South end of Trader's Row is Trader's End, where the less affluent, and less regulated Trades have their places of business.</p>","_id":"EBjGrWETUIr0x6a3"}
{"name":"Esteemed Guild of Dockers & Stevedores","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Docker's Guildhouse is situated at the @JournalEntry[South Dock], and is the formal residence of the \"Esteemed Guild of Dockers &amp; Stevedores\", there are currently 11 Members (In Good Standing).&nbsp; All 11 members use the Guildhouse as their home, partly because it is well provisionsed and maintained, and partly because they pay a tithe from their incomes to fund it whether they use it or not.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Guildhouse in ran by @Actor[Firennina \"Nina\" Skoranirasdottir], a dwarf who used to work as a Stevedore until her back was damaged in an accident.&nbsp; She walks with a slight leftward lean, and is very, very tetchy if anyone mentions it to her.&nbsp; With over 30 years good service as a Stevedore, and with the former Housemaster moving away to help establish a Guildhouse at Hagerdorf, it was only logical to appoint her as Housemaster, a duty she has fulfilled for the last 8 months.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>There are rumours that a Member has been passing information to Wreckers, Nina is busy trying to ferret out the traitor, and she will be welcoming of any information that would lead to their capture.</p>\n</section>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Guildhouse provides a hearty breakfast, and very solid evening meal; each Member In Good Standing is also entitled to a pint of Small Beer at each meal, and pint of rum on each Holiday.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Guildhouse gives offerings to @JournalEntry[Pater Teufel] on each @JournalEntry[Mitterfruhl] (Spring Equinox), and @JournalEntry[Mittherbst] (Autumnal Equinox).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The current Guildmaster is @Actor[Hannath Lankdorf], a sturdy women in her mid to late 30's who has been working the docks since she was in her early teens.&nbsp; She is assisted in her duties by her second in command, @Actor[Aleks Traeger].</p>","_id":"EiQd8b6Y8HI6Fb7a"}
{"name":"Lower Dock Street","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Running South along the river-front connecting the @JournalEntry[South Dock] to @JournalEntry[Threeways] is Lower Dock Street; one of the poorer areas of Halberst it is no less busy because of it.&nbsp; In fact it is one of the busier streets, seeing commerce to and from @JournalEntry[South Dock], the @JournalEntry[Esteemed Guild of Dockers &amp; Stevedores], the @JournalEntry[Landervogt Warehouse]. and the @JournalEntry[River Wardens] among others.</p>","_id":"Ez8QrhAaiEYCtJfR"}
{"name":"Cobbler's Workshop","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A long two-story building that has been very recently renovated.&nbsp; The ground floor is given over entirely to shoe-making, with benches around the walls separated into 3 areas; the upper floor contains four small single bunk rooms.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall] has recently, 6 months ago, paid for 4 Cobblers to move to Halberst, and has agreed to levy half the normal tax rate for the first year.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[House Kniehocher] owns the building, but has been an absentee landlord for many years, having withdrawn to their Shenstedt country estate over 20 years ago.&nbsp; However, with renewed investment in the town happening they have recently reopened their town house on @JournalEntry[Kennel Lane].</p>","img":"","_id":"FFv7F3xc3RnbQENp"}
{"name":"Karstadt Road #2","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A three-storey building, used as dwelling.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&lt;BLANK&gt;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"FTXvQ7thlFquAAot"}
{"name":"Unternehmer Warehouse","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>It is no accdient that the Unternehmer Warehouse sits right behind the @JournalEntry[Halberst Granary], @JournalEntry[House Unternehmer] has been the pre-eminent Grain and Dry Goods Merchant for the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Karstadt] and by extension the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Grauwerk] for almost 150 years.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The warehouse is managed by a retainer of House Unternehmer, @Actor[Karsten Stadler], a man in his late 30's who has been in Halberst for just over 20 years, 10 of those as an apprentice to his predecessor.&nbsp; Stadler is a Member (IGS) of the @JournalEntry[Learned Guild of Administrators &amp; Excisemen], and in fact is the Treasurer of such.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Twice a year the Head Chamberlain of House Unternehmer, one @Actor[Gilbrecht Scheffner], visits Halberst to go over the books, and make sure everything is in order.</p>","img":"","_id":"GWSotj25A5wtosGf"}
{"name":"Flickschuster's Shoe Repairs","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Flickschuster's Shoe Repairs</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Above Rudi's workshop is that of @Actor[Emmanuelle Flickschuster], she buys what little \"scrap\" leather Rudi has and uses it to repair, and enhance shoes and boots.&nbsp; Her work has a good repuation, and although she has never personally recieved the Graf's Warrant being in the same building as someone who has has not hurt her reputation, nor her ability to charge slightly above average for her services.</p>","img":"","_id":"GgjUO1bLosl1DpBb"}
{"name":"Waldenhof","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y3t0m7yb3h","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/10: Connected Background Material","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Not to be confused with the capital of Sylvania, Waldenhof is a medium sized mining town nestled half way up @JournalEntry[The Hagercrybs], sitting on one of the many tributaries to @JournalEntry[The Teufel].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>There are over a dozen mines of various sizes within a day or two of Waldenhof, and the hills and mountains hold many a ruined Village, Town and even Castles, some of which were lost to time hundreds of years ago.</p>","_id":"HIkoya6rKeTXibWm"}
{"name":"Karstadt Road #7","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>&lt;BLANK&gt;</p>","_id":"Hb8rTIG4cOk90EJe"}
{"name":"Reeve's House","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A two-storey building adjacent to the @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall], the lower floor has a small reception room, and a guard-post.&nbsp; The upper floor, has a private sitting room, and a bedroom, and a small cubby for the Reeve's housemaid.</p>","_id":"HoVT3H0wr2Rbt8O3"}
{"name":"Esser's Mews","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A long, two-storey building with two workshops on the ground floor for crafters.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The ground floor units are occupied by:</p>\n<p>@Actor[Rosalind Gaulichter],&nbsp; Candle-Maker, Member (IGS) of the @JournalEntry[Estimable Guild of Craftsmen],</p>\n<p>@Actor[Desdemona \"Dee\" Riverreed], a Basket-Weaver, Member (IGS) of the @JournalEntry[Estimable Guild of Craftsmen],</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The upper floor has three smaller units, they are occupied by:</p>\n<p>@Actor[Harbrand Schreiber], Scribe, Member (Lapsed) of the @JournalEntry[Learned Guild of Administrators &amp; Excisemen],</p>\n<p>@Actor[Magdalyna Truhenmacher] Carpenter (Chests), Member (IGS) of the @JournalEntry[Estimable Guild of Craftsmen].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The fifth unit is currently unoccupied, with rumours that the room is best by evil, following the grisly murder of the previous occupant, a Johannes Salzmann, the previous Geheinistag, a crime that is still to be solved.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","img":"","_id":"ICmiWqy9OlnrpTFi"}
{"name":"Porter's Kitchen","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>To the rear of the @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall] is an extension to the Hall, that servers as a Kitchen for the Hall.&nbsp; The infamously oppulent former Reeve, Alfreid Mohrtz (d. 2476 IC), decided that Officers of the Town should be provided with a lunch-time meal, and that it should be of a quality sufficiently commensurate with the importance of their functions.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Thus the Porter's Kitchen was added to the Hall, containing an extensive Kitche, Pantry and Dining Room.&nbsp; While opponents of Mohrts were keen to lambaste his profligacy none of them, including the man who succeeded him, has seen fit to do away with the Kitchen.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In fact it has been noted that providing the meal has increased the workflow of the Clerks of the Hall, as they now have no need to go out to the Inns of the town and have a liquid lunch.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Kitchen is managed by @Actor[Ermintrude \"Mindy\" Alepuddle] and her Porter @Actor[Matz Haffner].</p>","_id":"ISmQCXg9Rb89dcCy"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qgqh4rei9ki","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/08: Special Events","color":"#000000","name":"08: Special Events","children":["9Xk6mu5h6UJNq8y6"],"folderPath":["temp_syvf2bs7n7"]}},"content":"","_id":"IzARBJss0PjPFWlQ"}
{"name":"Lenkster's Court (East View)","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Mid way along its length, just past Morrslieb's Marsh, Baker's Row broadens out to almost form a natural courtyard, bounded on the East side the @JournalEntry[North Docks], the @JournalEntry[Halberst Granary], and the @JournalEntry[Unternehmer Warehouse].</p>","_id":"JROJN4JCxyM2WOdb"}
{"name":"Karstadt Road #1","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A two-storey building, used as dwelling.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&lt;BLANK&gt;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"Jf26PJvuhEofQfQ6"}
{"name":"Docker's Rise Stall","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.O8bHEC2Cd9pWog3i"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The outdoor Market has a Single Stall shared between @Actor[Rhet Kagelbruder] selling Fish, Eels and Teufel Crab, and @Actor[Juniper Meadowherb] selling wild herbs.</p>","_id":"KI6eCo31FOW3iXOU"}
{"name":"Schrodinger's","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Sitting next to, and slightly back from, the @JournalEntry[Templemann Almshouse] is a two-storey building with a weathered door, once coated in vibrant green paint.&nbsp; The house likewise looks slightly rundown, the upper floor windows is stained and dusty.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Actor[Paulus Schrodinger]{Creepy Schrodinger} lives here, and has for over 30 years.&nbsp; Two generations of Halberst children have grown up knowing to avoid Schrodinger's house, and not to speak to him in the street.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Gossip: 1</p>\n<p>Roughly twice a week Schrodinger visits the various Markets in Halberst and buys food and drink, and returns to his house.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Gossip: 2</p>\n<p>A candle or lamp can be seen glowing brightly in the upper floor window long into the night.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Gossip: 3</p>\n<p>Sometimes the glowing light takes on a vibrant blueish hue.&nbsp;</p>\n</section>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</section>","img":"","_id":"KnYGQA3dHcDrr893"}
{"name":"Temple Street #3","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.A2MbiPSlD3tK0yVO"},"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Temple Street is named after the @JournalEntry[Temple of Sigmar] that sits upon it, technically more a Square than a Street the erroneuous name has defied all attempts at correction, including a writ by former Reeve, Kasparus Landervogt, that stipulated a 1d fine for using the incorrect name.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","img":"","_id":"KueWfth4sZ5cWzeQ"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000","name":"04: Organisations & Officialdom","children":["sCACRUVEc69x6cG0","jbWj6vabNpNgHPE9","gItZPZU2CNr1ohiz","tvdVchGIhADj0N5E","EiQd8b6Y8HI6Fb7a","eTwnVBlboCUbIz6p","mPbhaAtrTt5ybhqN","csoJAdCOMCw0kSGQ","k6A14Yfwnqkb8W6M","kkMonqvX9sqUn9M1","4ChniG9Q2ylM0cZ7","ZccfX8dr8nwwgWnx","fZq3ZmxkpYarHiYk","ISmQCXg9Rb89dcCy","Qss944Ua3LQO35J7","uz1j2Qpwek2sO3E3","ceD8AJqFe747glFN","yf6ypUbiaA3RT366"],"folderPath":["temp_syvf2bs7n7"]}},"content":"","_id":"L8RaHYel0S210kWV"}
{"name":"Leitschenker House","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Leitschenker House sit at the top of the @JournalEntry[Dagger's Drop] where it meets @JournalEntry[Guild Street].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>It is a three-storey building with one entrance adjacent to Dagger's Drop and another entrance on the opposite side of the building.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Ground floor, and first floor are the family home of the &lt;BLANK&gt;.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The 2nd Floor is split into 3 single-room garrets.</p>\n<p>1: &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>\n<p>2: &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>\n<p>3: &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>","_id":"LFhBcz7F4roDd1bi"}
{"name":"Morrslieb's Marsh","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_56jqb4pyr6l","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/05: River Front","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A small, shallow Marsh situationed between The @JournalEntry[Fisherman's Guild] and The @JournalEntry[River Wardens] Station; It has proven to be strenuously resistant to being cleared, over the years several attempts have been made; but the marsh soon re-establisheses itself, and any structure built over it is ar more prone to rot and decay than usual.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Local legend has it that on Hexensnacht and Geheimnisnacht noxious vapour rise from the marsh and causes illness.&nbsp; Accordingly the area is cordened off on those nights, river traffic is halted during nightfall, and The&nbsp; @JournalEntry[River Reaver Inn] locks its doors and shutters a good half-candle before dusk, and does not reopen them until well after dawn.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>The legend is true, during Hexensnacht and Geheimnisnacht the Marsh is a conduit between worlds, allowing vapours from the realm of the dead to pass through to the mortal realm.&nbsp; If the night-sky is clear of cloud the rising vapours can been seen to take on the shapes of men, and will wander the river-front - never more that a few feet from the Marsh - and attack those who get too close.&nbsp; &nbsp;These shapes are in fact @Actor[Ghost]s.</p>\n</section>","img":"worlds/uber-chron/images/Halberst/Hal_Morrslieb%27s_Marsh_River.png","_id":"LpeIXGBaLfwJp34Q"}
{"name":"Schrader's Outfitters","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>@Actor[Enghardt Schrader] is a bespoke Tailer, he has business premises on @JournalEntry[Trader's Row].&nbsp; A three-storey building with a narrow front; the ground-floor is the Tailor's Shop, including a fitting room; the first-floor is the workroom where he crafts the garments, and his wife, @Actor[Elspeth Schrader] assists and adds, prmarily for the ladies of Halberst, embroidery and lace.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Both Enghardt and Elspeth are holders of a @JournalEntry[Graf's Warrant], giving them the prestige of being the only business premises in Halberst with two Warrants.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Schrader's supplies offical tabbards to the @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall] for the various branches of officialdom; and sashes of office to the various guilds.&nbsp; In fact they are so busy they are looking to move premises, perhaps to the larger two-storey building on @JournalEntry[Trader's End]</p>","_id":"MoaYEhXsC41PuaHq"}
{"name":"Krudener's Apothecarium","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Krudener's Apothecarium</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Opposite Rudi's workshop is a two-storey wattle and daube building occupied by @Actor[Ekaterina Krudener], the town's apothecary.&nbsp; She has been in residence for 5 years, after moving to Halberst from Karstadt, claiming that both the Sage and the Thyme here were far superior.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Ekaterina holds a @JournalEntry[Graf's Warrant],&nbsp;</p>","_id":"N7Lc26TYXXm0f4ym"}
{"name":"Radecker's Cottage","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The cottage quite obviously started out as a single dwelling, but has been split into two dwellings; the lower floor is occupied by @Actor[Harbrand Schreiber] the town scribe, and inveterate gambler; the upper floor is occupied by @Actor[Rosalind Gaulichter] a candle-maker; both have stalls within @JournalEntry[Esser's Mews].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Their rental agreements with @JournalEntry[House Radecker] include clauses for the rental of the cottages.</p>\n</section>","img":"","_id":"NHXN0fQHgmtsmc5u"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pxh26pbtbf","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/06: Taverns & Inns","color":"#000000","name":"06: Taverns & Inns","children":["Unao1NEqcEw7bqRX","eKb71QM28ioQSQqM","5DP17ivxvcIUGRZu","QArPVqbxGS3oDI5Q","d0W3yKJdqA3vFa6w","XbXXaV7NbeaqDW9q","iUmBVi2WaArXda8H","tnUMa0adTLfei8Uc","6Yn0Fb7Ay5BjsKac","blpajtouO9h8T36I"],"folderPath":["temp_syvf2bs7n7"]}},"content":"","_id":"OCUpiiKI5Xmc8WGI"}
{"name":"Barchenweber's Weavers","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>@Actor[Gerhardt Barchenweber] is a master-weaver, and has a @JournalEntry[Graf's Warrant] for his work.&nbsp; Notable patrons from as far afield as @JournalEntry[Ubersreik] and @JournalEntry[Auerswald] have commissioned work from him.</p>","_id":"OE06EOUJXWwHkZft"}
{"name":"Radecker's Yard","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Situated right on @JournalEntry[Threeways] Radecker's Yard is home to a small courtyard with three buildings:</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A small two-floor cottage, @JournalEntry[Radecker's Cottage] is slightly run-down, and worse for wear.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A long, two-story, building containing 5 small workshops for various crafters, called @JournalEntry[Esser's Mews].</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A two-storey building, that is well-maintaoned, and carries the sign of the @JournalEntry[Drunken Rat Tavern].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","img":"worlds/uber-chron/images/Halberst/Hal_Cutpurse_Yard.png","_id":"Oo13ehwcpsDuvWDn"}
{"name":"Temple Street #2","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.A2MbiPSlD3tK0yVO"},"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Temple Street is named after the @JournalEntry[Temple of Sigmar] that sits upon it, technically more a Square than a Street the erroneuous name has defied all attempts at correction, including a writ by former Reeve, Kasparus Landervogt, that stipulated a 1d fine for using the incorrect name.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As well as the Temple Of Sigmar, Temple Street is home to the @JournalEntry[Scythe &amp; Sigmar Inn], and the @JournalEntry[Priest's House].</p>","img":"","_id":"Q2kH0FTDUNO0JHDJ"}
{"name":"River Reaver Inn","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pxh26pbtbf","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/06: Taverns & Inns","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><strong>Sign: </strong>A Reaver attacking a River Barge.</p>\n<p><strong>Proprietor:</strong> @Actor[Sigrid Krugmann]</p>\n<p><strong>Staff:</strong> Elmer Krugmann (m 13), Edythe Schrader (f 14)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">Close to the river Teufal, on Baker's Row, The River Reaver caters mostly to those who travel, live and work on the river. There is a Bunk-Room capable of sleeping 14, 2 quad-rooms, and 1 private room.&nbsp; The food and drink are hearty but nothing fancy.&nbsp; The ale however is excellent, widely reputed to be the best in Halberst' Reaver's Bite is a hearty, malty pint, brewed as joint venture between Sigrid Krugmann (the proprietor of The River reaver) and @Actor[Tobias Bachmann] (the current head baker at @JournalEntry[Brotbacker's Bakery]{Brotbaker's}).</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0798%; height: 128px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\" colspan=\"3\"><strong>The River Reaver</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Lodgings &amp; Services</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Meals</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Drinks</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Bunkroom Bed: 10d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Porridge / Gruel: 4d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Standard Ale: 3d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Quad Room: 4/- each&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Stew and Bread: 1/-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Reaver's Bite: 7d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Private Room: 10/-&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Bread, Fruit &amp; Cheese: 1/-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Spirits 1/4 Pint: 1/-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Hot Bath: 6d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Roast Platter: 2/5d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Wine, Bottle, Cheap: 1/3d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Clothes Service: 2d per item</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"QArPVqbxGS3oDI5Q"}
