{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_56jqb4pyr6l","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/05: River Front","color":"#000000","name":"05: River Front","children":["843afJWCFgAQpzmU","LpeIXGBaLfwJp34Q","XEfkvLKevGtPwfQZ","YyjrSYQROKCRR8l5"],"folderPath":["temp_syvf2bs7n7"]}},"content":"","_id":"Qr3VNPlV9n0TYXkR"}
{"name":"River Wardens","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Technically it is the River &amp; Road Wardens, but in recent years Graf Steirlich von Bruner has appointed part of the town Militia to patrol the roads, leaving only the River Wardens in residence.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Wardens have authority from @JournalEntry[Gottheim] through to @JournalEntry[Flechtben], but the two Wardens stationed at the @JournalEntry[Leche] Docks patrol up to Flechtben.&nbsp; There are 4 wardens employed here, led by Warden-Captain @Actor[Jorne Reifsneider], Wardens @Actor[Talima Langstrom], and @Actor[Engel Adelhof], and Recruit @Actor[Axelbrand \"Ax\" Sandyhill].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Wardens-House is served by @Actor[Viggo Rohrig], technically employed by the @JournalEntry[River Reaver Inn], but permanently assigned to the Wardens.</p>","img":"","_id":"Qss944Ua3LQO35J7"}
{"name":"Karstadt Road","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The main West Road out of Halberst leads deeper into the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Karstadt], and eventually to @JournalEntry[Karstadt] itself.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Within Halberst it is the road on which the more prosperous dwellings and businesses are located, just beyond the gate is @JournalEntry[Stallknecht's Sables] and its paddock, with enough room for 12 horses.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Beyond that is a series of small tennat-farms, farming produce and livestock for the town.&nbsp; On the road roughly 1/2 mile out of town is @JournalEntry[Bauerkurner's Mill], a windmill that serves the farmers.</p>","_id":"RS4t4a2ac3fiLRbv"}
{"name":"Tammerhorn House","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Tammerhorn House is a ramshackle building that looks as likely to fall down in the next high wind as it does to stand upright.&nbsp; Inside the house is in no better condition, and is actually used by those who otherwise be homeless.&nbsp; The building is designed to sleep 12, 4 on each floor, but has been known to sleep as many as 20, with additional sleeping space being created by using hammocks.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The building is subject to a \"peppercorn rent\" of just 2 Crowns a year; and is paid via the @JournalEntry[Tammerhorn Trust] based in @JournalEntry[Auerswald]; the trust also funds an annual inspection to be carried out by the @JournalEntry[Estimable Guild of Craftsmen].&nbsp;</p>","_id":"SG1Pm49RnpIGnwHE"}
{"name":"Gottheim Road #1-5","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Above @JornalEntry[Scherbart's Barber-Surgeon] are two more storeys used as dwellings.&nbsp; Accessed from the side of the building using external stairs.&nbsp; The Dwellings are occupied by the following:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1: 2nd Floor, two rooms, occupied by &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>\n<p>2: 2nd Floor, two rooms, occupied by &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>\n<p>3: 3rd Floor, one room, occupied by @Actor[Adelina \"Lina\" Scherbart]</p>\n<p>4: 3rd Floor, two rooms, occupied by &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>","_id":"UbsYANKvKCd4npxF"}
{"name":"*** INN TEMPLATE ***","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pxh26pbtbf","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/06: Taverns & Inns","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><strong>Sign: </strong>A Reaver attacking a River Barge.</p>\n<p><strong>Proprietor:</strong> Sigrid Krugmann</p>\n<p><strong>Staff:</strong> Elmer Krugmann (m 13), Edythe Schrader (f 14)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">Close to the river Teufal, on Baker's Row, The River Reaver caters mostly to those who travel, live and work on the river. There is a Bunk-Room capable of sleeping 14, 2 quad-rooms, and 1 private room.&nbsp; The food and drink are hearty but nothing fancy.&nbsp; The ale however is excellent, widely reputed to be the best in Halberst' Reaver's Bite is a hearty, malty pint, brewed as joint venture between Sigrid Krugmann (the proprietor of The River reaver) and Tobias Bachmann (the current head baker at Brotbackers).</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0798%; height: 128px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\" colspan=\"3\"><strong>The River Reaver</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Lodgings &amp; Services</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Meals</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Drinks</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Bunkroom Bed: 10d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Porridge / Gruel: 4d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Standard Ale: 3d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Quad Room: 4/- each&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Stew and Bread: 1/-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Reaver's Bite: 7d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Private Room: 10/-&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Bread, Fruit &amp; Cheese: 1/-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Spirits 1/4 Pint: 1/-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Hot Bath: 6d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Roast Platter: 2/5d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Wine, Bottle, Cheap: 1/3d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Clothes Service: 2d per item</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"Unao1NEqcEw7bqRX"}
{"name":"Coachman's Corner","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Where the @JournalEntry[Grauwerk Road] (North) meets the @JournalEntry[Karstadt Road] (West) is Coachman's Corner, named such as many a novice Coachman has run afoul of the sharp bend, and uneven road.&nbsp; Slightly to the South of Coachman's Corner is The @JournalEntry[Two Soldiers Inn], and to the East is the @JournalEntry[Halberst Garrison].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Standing tall on the verge at Coachman's Corner is @JournalEntry[Tammerhorn House].</p>","img":"worlds/uber-chron/images/Halberst/Hal_Coachman%27s_Corner.png","_id":"Uql2LCSKbTFJ1bXq"}
{"name":"Temple Street #1","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Temple Street is named after the @JournalEntry[Temple of Sigmar] that sits upon it, technically more a Square than a Street the erroneuous name has defied all attempts at correction, including a writ by former Reeve, Kasparus Landervogt, that stipulated a 1d fine for using the incorrect name.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As well as the Temple Of Sigmar, Temple Street is home to variuos buildings, both domestic and commercial, includind: @JournalEntry[Haffner's Pottery], the @JournalEntry[Templemann Almshouse], the 'JournalEntry[Priest's House], and @JournalEntry[Barchenweber's Weavers].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>","_id":"VNto3OvroNeXQI7o"}
{"name":"Guild Street","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Guild Street heads South off of the @JournalEntry[Karstadt Road] and rises slightly up towards the @JournalEntry[Guilder's Market] which sits in front of the impressive @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall], the administartive centre of Halberst and the seat of Reeve @Actor[Constanza Landervogt].&nbsp; This street is better maintained than most in Halberst, and is also better patrolled by the @JournalEntry[Halberst Garrison].</p>","_id":"VrWtWBwZgYdiVDzB"}
{"name":"Beggar's Rise","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Connecting @JournalEntry[Guild Street], @JournalEntry[Trader's Row], and @JournalEntry[Artisan's Corner] is Beggar's Rise, a completely mundane stretch of street, flanked on one side by some overgrown weeds, and on the other a drop into the side of @JournalEntry[House Kniehocher].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The street is named because it is the only place in Halberst where it is legal to beg, because of that, and the currennt unstable economic climate, Beggar's Row is often home to 4 or 5 Beggars at a time; there have been some complaints from the Townsmen that they should be \"moved on\".</p>","img":"worlds/uber-chron/images/Halberst/Hal_Beggar%27s_Rise.png","_id":"W5qKMbdrxSMupBRV"}
{"name":"Docker's Rise","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A series of wooden stairs and platform leads from @JournalEntry[South Dock] upto the @JournalEntry[Lower Gottheim Road] adjacent to the @JournalEntry[South Gate].&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The small @JournalEntry[Docker's Rise Market] is situated on the gorund floor of the building here, on the lower floor of the @JournalEntry[South Gate Watch-House].&nbsp; On the rise itself is the @JournalEntry[Docker's Rise Stall], a shabby, run-down market stall, that nevertheless seems constantly busy.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"WAiBDEkdJ03mIzQu"}
{"name":"Trader's Row","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Running parallel to the Guild Street is Trader's Row, home to independent traders and entrepeneurs.</p>","_id":"WOJW3ftQmbnQESNm"}
{"name":"Upper Dock Street","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Upper Dock Street links @JournalEntry[Lower Dock Street] with @JournalEntry[Threeways], and @JournalEntry[The Stump], providing access to @JournalEntry[Kahnsmann's Portage Services], and @JournalEntry[Radecker's Yard],&nbsp;@JournalEntry[House Landervogt] is also situated on Upper Dock Street.</p>","_id":"WmBF4zzErfqBn6h6"}
{"name":"North Docks","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_56jqb4pyr6l","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/05: River Front","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>With two building, slightly larger than the one at @JournalEntry[South Dock], and with a significant sized dock-front the North Dock has over 4 times the storage capacity of the South Dock area.&nbsp; However, North Dock is newer than South Dock and tradition dictates that the Dock-Master oversees the South Dock.&nbsp; Accordingly the North Dock is managed by @Actor[Aleks Traeger] Member (IGS) of the @JournalEntry[Esteemed Guild of Dockers &amp; Stevedores], and second-in-command to @Actor[Hannath Lankdorf].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Aleks is assisted by several Members of the @JournalEntry[Esteemed Guild of Dockers &amp; Stevedores].</p>","_id":"XEfkvLKevGtPwfQZ"}
