{"name":"Twelve Daggers Tavern","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pxh26pbtbf","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/06: Taverns & Inns","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><strong>Sign: </strong>A Circle of Twelve Daggers, with their points joining in the centre.</p>\n<p><strong>Proprietor:</strong> @Actor[Siegmund \"Ziggy\" Kuppler]</p>\n<p><strong>Staff:</strong> @Actor[Vargaz Untroksson]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With three floors and exterior porches given over to Bars and Snugs The Twelve Daggers is the largest drinking establishment in Halberst.&nbsp; The ground floor main bar typically has some form of musical entertainment going on, and is often lively or even raucus becasue of it.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Daggers offers by far the widest range of drinks in Halberst, and attracts clientele of all social stations because of it.&nbsp; Indeed some of the better infomed patrons often marvel at the range of drinks available, with drinks from as far afield as Kislev, Norsca, and even Albion and Araby routinely available for purchase... ...at a price of course.</p>\n<hr />\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Price List</strong></span></p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1292%; height: 416px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 51.2624%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Drink Prices</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7127%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Food Prices</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; text-align: left; height: 16px;\">Ale, Standard, Pint:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">3d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; text-align: left; height: 16px;\">Cold Platter, Cheese, Ham, Apple</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">10d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Ale, Premium, Pint:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">4d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Breakfast, Porridge, Toast, Jam</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">8d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Ale, Black Sunset, Pint:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">6d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Stew, Lamb with Vegetables</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">1/-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Ale, Olde Dog, Pint:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">6d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Roast, with Vegetables</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">1/4d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Ale, Woodsman's Folly, Pint:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">5d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Mixed Fry, Sausage, Bacon, Eggs</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">1/6d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Dwarven Ale, Frostfire (served hot), Pint:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">7d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Sweet Buns</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">5d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Dwarven Ale, Skorlina's Malt, Pint:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">7d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Fruit Scones, with Butter</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">7d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Cider, Apple, Pint:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">5d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Weissertopf, Sweet</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">8d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Cider, Pear, Pint:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">6d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Weissertopf, Savoury</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">10d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Wine, Standard, Bottle (4 Goblets):</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">11d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Wine, Good, Bottle (4 Goblets):</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/8d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Wine, Excellent, Bottle, (4 Goblets):</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">2/10d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Wine, Bretonian, Bottle (4 Goblets):</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">3/2d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.7127%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Drinks Prices</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Wine, Tilean, Bottle (4 Goblets):</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">4/-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Honkitzos (Kislev), Grape Vodka, Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Brandy, Suderberg, Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">10d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Cztarkha (Kislev), Aged Vodka, Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/10d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Brandy, Almagora (Estalian), Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/3d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Khortytsa (Kislev), Cinnamon Vodka, Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">2/4d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Brandy, Gransette (Bretonian), Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/8d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Svedkoning (Norsca), Cherry Vodka, Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">2/7d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Brandy, Blauschwalbe, Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">2/-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Iskvardricke (Norse), Juniper Ale, Pint:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/4d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Obstler, Apple (Averland), Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">11d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">Zavstravon (Kislev), Peach Ale, Pint:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/2d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Obstler, Plum (Nordland), Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/4d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Arak (Araby), Aniseed, Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/6d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Ronmiel (Estalian), Honey &amp; Rum, Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/2d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Palo de Molena (Estalian), Orange, Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">2/4d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Medean Mistra (Araby), Anise, Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/9d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40.4773%; height: 16px;\">Silovitz (Kislev), Damsons, Shot:</td>\n<td style=\"width: 10.7851%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1/4d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 37.8151%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 9.89768%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">@JournalEntry[Doing The Round]</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Infamous among the patrons of the Twelve Daggers is a challenge known a \"Doing The Round\", that is drinking one standard measure of each drink the Twelve Daggers serves.&nbsp; Anyone capable of doing so not only gets their money back, but also gets their name, engraved on the \"Roll of Honour\" - a wooden carved scroll that hangs behind the bar.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cost of \"Doing The Round\": 2GC 2/11d</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So far there are only 3 names on the Roll Of Honour: @Actor[Balagrom Hargonsson], @Actor[Andris Trabant], and Nikolas Fliegermann.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">At the bottom of the Scroll is a section marked \"Fallen Heroes\" under which is one name: Lucius Stortzer.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Anyone asking about the names on the Roll of Honour can find the following information with a successful <strong>Gossip Test: Average +20 Difficulty</strong>:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Balagrim Hargonnson:</strong> local Silversmith and Engraver, lives up at Artisan's Corner.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Andris Trabant:</strong> Sergeant at the @JournalEntry[Halberst Garrison], renowned for his drinking prowess.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Nikolas Fliegermann:</strong> passing through Halberst two years ago, even now the raucous night when he Did The Round is fondly remembered, not least becasue @Actor[Siegmund \"Ziggy\" Kuppler]{Ziggy} offered a free round to everyone on the house.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Lucius Stortzer: </strong>a minor noble, who unfortunately passed away just 4 drinks short of completing \"The Round\".</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n</section>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although technically illegal, practicality permits prostitution, and The Daggers is home to Halberst's Brothel, with 4 working girls, who when brothel business is slow double up as barmaids.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Daggers is also home to @Actor[August Leichmann], @Actor[Rufus Pfeifer],&nbsp; @Actor[Maida Sanger], and @Actor[Thadeus Trommeler], a band of musicians who provide live music in the main bar every night.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Dagger is a front for Halberst's criminal underbelly, a gang know as the @JournalEntry[12 Daggers]; it is believed 12 of them.&nbsp; Despite several raids by the Town Guard and Grauwerk Militia nothing has ever been found of this elusive group.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n</section>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","img":"","_id":"XbXXaV7NbeaqDW9q"}
{"name":"Artisan's Corner","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Close to the North Wall, where @JournalEntry[Kennel Lane] meets @JournalEntry[Beggar's Rise] you'll find Artisan's Corner; a few buildings that are home to some of the elite craftsmen of the town.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Here can be found @JournalEntry[Fellhauer's Premium Leather Goods], @JournalEntry[Flickschuster's Shoe Repairs], @JournalEntry[Krudener's Apothecarium], and @JournalEntry[Halberst Engravers &amp; Silversmiths].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Perched on a slight rise of land behind Krudener's, and accessed via a worn and rickety wooden staircase, is @JournalEntry[Steinschneider's], a single room, poorly maintained building.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","img":"worlds/uber-chron/images/Halberst/Hal_Artisan_Corner.png","_id":"Xk7C6pnI2MhgdBH8"}
{"name":"South Dock","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_56jqb4pyr6l","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/05: River Front","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The South Dock is mainly used for smaller goods that can easily be carried by one or two people.&nbsp; It only has mooring for one vessel at a time.&nbsp; There is an open fronted warehouse for sturdy goods, and a twin-roofed long warehouse for more perishable goods, the @JournalEntry[Landervogt Warehouse].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Dock is managed my @Actor[Hannath Lankdorf], a sturdy 3rd generation Stevedore with a srong Kemperbad accent.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Lore: Reikland roll challenging difficulty to identify accent.</p>\n</section>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>She is assisted by @Actor[Edegar Reiss],&nbsp; and @Actor[Reuben Bethz] who handle the heavy lifting.&nbsp; The Stevedores charge 1d per item if it can be carried by one man, or 3d per item if it requires two men.&nbsp; Attempts to avoid paying the Stevedores usually results in the Town Militia being called in, there is nearly always one or two militiamen posted at the docks during daylight hours.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As Halberst is still the primary river-trade hub for @JournalEntry[Duchy of Karstadt], and - because of the poor mooring at Leche - the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Grauwerk] the @JournalEntry[Graf Steirlich von Bruner] makes sure that @JournalEntry[Halberst] is well defended and that all applicable taxes are paid.</p>","_id":"YyjrSYQROKCRR8l5"}
{"name":"Trader's Row #3&4","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"gm-notes":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A two-storey building, the entrance to the ground floor is on Trader's Row, the entrance to the upper floor is on @JournalEntry[Reeve's Lane] via an more recently conctructed wooden porch that, regardless of its more recent construction, is showing signs of disrepair.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>#3: Ground Floor</p>\n<p>&lt;BLANK&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<p>#4: Upper Floor</p>\n<p>@Actor[Polyana Slune] has recently fallen on hard times, just over a year ago her benefactor and lover Kasparus Landervogt passed away.&nbsp; &nbsp;As Kasparus was her only source of income, and her only friend, she is now in a precarious position. Polyana has a maid-servant, Greta Metzener, and has enough money to pay the girl, her rent, and living costs for about 4 months.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Kasparus was visiting @JournalEntry[Ubersreik] on business, and was staying in the @JournalEntry[Emperor's Rest Hostel] when he forst saw Polyana, working as a chambermad. He fell in love with her immediately, and extended his visit to Ubersreik by a week to woo her.&nbsp; When he returned to Halberst he rented rooms for her on Trader's Row, and installed her as his mistress.&nbsp; &nbsp;He even managed to keep it a secret from his wife, @Actor[Constanza Landervogt]{Constanza} for a while, but his frequent daytime visits to her rooms soon had tongues wagging.&nbsp;</p>\n</section>","img":"","_id":"ZKyD4kpw5oqQZN22"}
{"name":"Karstadt","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y3t0m7yb3h","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/10: Connected Background Material","color":"#000000"}},"content":null,"_id":"ZYsJxE2G1OZvg6e4"}
{"name":"Dagger's Drop","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Connecting @JournalEntry[Guild Street] with @JournalEntry[Upper Gottheim Road] and winding among the various building of the @JournalEntry[Twelve Daggers Tavern] is a series of wooden steps and platforms know locally as Dagger's Drop.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>At the top of the Drop is a three-storey building with entrances to the South and North, this is the @JournalEntry[Leitschenker House]</p>","_id":"Zan7tayCp0j3rvpE"}
{"name":"Learned Guild of Administrators & Excisemen","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Learned Guild of Administrators &amp; Excisemen has a small records office in the @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall].&nbsp; If there is one thing the guild members are good at it is the organisation and recording of information; as such they have long realised that having a huge organisational board is inefficient, and often counter-productive.&nbsp; Accordingly they have only three officers, a Guild Master, a Convener, and a Treasurer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Guild has three classes of Members: Members (In Good Standing), fully paid up and active Members; Member (Lapsed), Members who are either no longer active in the field but have maintained their dues, or active Members who have fallen behind in their dues; Member (Affiliate), Members who pay no dues, and have no voting rights, these are usually Officers of other Guilds, whose duties entail administration and collection dues from their respective Guilds and their Clients.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Guild Master is responsible for liaising with the Reeve, and the leaders of other Guilds to ensure that business of facilitating the flow of business in Halberst is as smooth as possible.&nbsp; The current Guildmaster is @Actor[Constanza Landervogt].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Convener has the duty of calling Guild Meetings, and managing the flow of business of those meetings; in the event that a sufficient number of Guild Members have registered a vote of No Confidence in an Officer it is the Convener who arranges for the resulting election.&nbsp; The Convener is alo responsible for ensuring that all official Guild paperwork is compliant with both Guild regulations and local law.&nbsp; The current Convener is @Actor[Harbrand Schreiber].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Treasurer is responsible for ensuring all Guild Members have paid their dues, for ensuring that clients of Members have paid their bills, and for initiating legal proceeding if any have failed to so.&nbsp; The current Treasurer is @Actor[Klara Geldenrektor].</p>","_id":"ZccfX8dr8nwwgWnx"}
{"name":"South-Gate Alley","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>To the side of the @JournalEntry[South Gate Watch-House] is a narrow ally, containing two two-story dwellings.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The first is a small dwelling with a single room on each floor &lt;BLANK&gt;.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The second is a larger building with two rooms on each floor, and the upper and lower floor are being used as separate dwellngs &lt;BLANK&gt;.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Both buildings are owned by the @JournalEntry[Esteemed Guild of Dockers &amp; Stevedores], to be used for Members of the Guild; however with recent falls in dock trade all current Guild Members reside within the Guild House, and so these dwellings are rented out to make money for the Guild.</p>\n</section>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>As of the last Municipal Inspection, carried out by the Guild of Craftsmen the smaller dwelling has been deemed to be \"unsafe\" requiring the Guild to undertake repairs.&nbsp; They have so far avoided doing so.</p>\n</section>","_id":"ZdBaSnABgMMY5bn7"}
{"name":"Helena Garkoche","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>@Actor[Helena Garkoche] is a purveyor of fine preserves.&nbsp; While most households in the Empire will have some skill at making preserves, Helena has turned it into a very profitable business.&nbsp; She is proud to be the holder of a @JournalEntry[Graf's Warrant].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Originally based in @JournalEntry[Ubersreik], Helena moved her business to Halberst just over two years ago, primarly to take advantage of the better quality of water, but also because Halberst has well established Orchards, and the Wild herbs hereabouts cabn be used much fresher than anything she can get in Ubersreik, and for lesser cost.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The entire ground floor of her house is given over to the production of preserves, and she has extensive trade with both @JournalEntry[Haffner's Pottery], and @JournalEntry[Docker's Rise Stall]{Juniper Meadowherb}.</p>","_id":"aXhgMTvUsuXcm1e7"}
{"name":"Kniehocher Tannery","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>About a half-mile out of town to the North, sitting on the bank of&nbsp; @JournalEntry[The Teufel], is the Kniehocher Tannery.&nbsp; Situated where it is to ensure that any run-off from the curing vats does not polute the riverfront of Halberst the Tannery is constantly surrounded by the stench of the Tanning process.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Tannery is run by Master Tanner @Actor[Rosamunde Gerber], and her assistants.&nbsp; While the land has always belonged to @JournalEntry[House Kniehocher] they were, in effect, absentee landlords, who really only cared that they got their yearly rent and tithe.&nbsp; However, the recent arrival in Halberst of @Actor[Heidrun Kniehocher] has changed all that, the House is now taking a more directly hands-on approach to the tannery, and has even installed a Master Tanner, @Actor[Griswold Erchenmeker], to run the Tannery; much to Roasamunde's chagrin.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Tannery building are long overdue some essential maintenance, and accidents have been increasing of late; so far Griswold has shown no interest in rectifying the situation, and in fact seems more interested in cutting the amount spent on repairs to show a healthier profit on the books.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Other staff include:</p>\n<p>Viggo Borkschelder: produces Tannin from Oak, Beech and Ash bark.</p>\n<p>Lorna Lohmuller: mixes the Lime for stripping the fur for smooth leather.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Were Rosamude able to set up a new Tannery all of the local staff would go with her, leaving the Kniehocher Tannery in dire straits, and earning the animosity of Heidrun Kniehocher.</p>\n</section>","_id":"ajS3vJsVya9MY77a"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y3t0m7yb3h","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/10: Connected Background Material","color":"#000000","name":"10: Connected Background Material","children":["w7A3rGhkuIWdWRBa","z8MOQDusZ1uR9GC7","ihl1NOOEC2zP96dM","ZYsJxE2G1OZvg6e4","ujA41H67z3u7Rc2o","HIkoya6rKeTXibWm"],"folderPath":["temp_syvf2bs7n7"]}},"content":"","_id":"alMfutAwStFNODDO"}
{"name":"Docker's Rise Market","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The indoor market has 4 stalls:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Actor[Nicolette Altwender], a repairer and seller of used clothing,</p>\n<p>@Actor[Rikart Rastelbinder], a tinker, and repairer of pots and pans,</p>\n<p>@Actor[Markus Schettler], a maker of Wooden Bowls, and Member (IGS) of the @JournalEntry[Estimable Guild of Craftsmen],</p>\n<p>@Actor[Gretchen Remenschlager], a Belt Maker, and Member (Lapsed) of the @JournalEntry[Estimable Guild of Craftsmen].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"bEYKmHCbaKpnu6Ze"}
{"name":"Wandering Bretonian Stables","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pxh26pbtbf","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/06: Taverns & Inns","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The @JournalEntry[Wandering Bretonian Inn] has two stables, one on the @JournalEntry[Grauwerk Road] with the rest of the Inn's outbuildings, and a second on @JournalEntry[Lenkster's Row].</p>\n<p>The second stable is only used when the main one is at capacity, but this can happen once or twice every week, depending on the coaching scedules.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The main Stable is manned by by Stable-Master and Blacksmith @Actor[Wilhelm Beschlager], he is assisted around the Stable-Yard by his younger son @Actor[Sigbert Beschlager], his elder daughter @Actor[Lena Beschlager].&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Stabling, per Horse, per night: 10d.</p>\n<p>Shoeing of Horse: 4d per hoof.</p>","img":"","_id":"blpajtouO9h8T36I"}
{"name":"Stadtarbeiterhof","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Stadtarbeiterhof sits right next door to the @JournalEntry[West-Gate Watch House].&nbsp; It is a three-storey building with a large double-door on the ground floor, on the left side of the building is an external wooden staircase leading up to the first floor.&nbsp; This is the \"Town Worker Hall\", that contains the tools and equipment used by the small cadre of the workers employed by Halberst to maintain the roads and building owned by the town.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The ground floor contains a workshop area with shovels, brooms and other tools, as well as three hand-carts, and some wooden barricades that are used for closing off Temple Street during festival days.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The first floor contains an office area, with hand-drawn plans of the town streets, building owned by the town, the boundaries of the town's authority mounted on the wall, and a central desk with current projects etc.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The thrid-floor is a small garret area, with dividers making 4 sleeping areas, each containing a bed, a footlocker, and low cabinet for belongings.&nbsp;&nbsp;Currently three of the beds are used, by the Clerk of Works @Actor[Klaus Angestellter], and his assistants, Manfred Tagner and Kristyna Mietlinger.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The workers can be seen around town on a daily basis, wearing tabbards with the Halberst Town Crest, with crossed shovels.&nbsp; Like all town employees the workers are entitled to a free lunch at the @JournalEntry[Porter's Kitchen] seven days a week.</p>","_id":"ceD8AJqFe747glFN"}
{"name":"Halberst Gaol","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.aKr3WnBEiF4d0qZc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Sitting on @JournalEntry[Coachman's Corner] opposite the @JournalEntry[Two Soldiers Inn] is the Halberst Garrison.</p>\n<p>Standing slightly apart and to the side is the Halberst Gaol; most likely to be used for rowdy drunks, it has been many months since any serious criminal activity occured in Halberst.</p>","_id":"csoJAdCOMCw0kSGQ"}
{"name":"Scythe & Sigmar Inn","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pxh26pbtbf","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/06: Taverns & Inns","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><strong>Sign: </strong>A Twin Tailed Comet with a Scythe crossed over it.</p>\n<p><strong>Proprietor:</strong> @Actor[Ragen Holzbein]</p>\n<p><strong>Staff:</strong> &lt;TO SORT&gt;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">Situated on @JournalEntry[Temple Street #1] the Scyth and Sigmar is popular with pilgrims visiting the @JournalEntry[Temple of Sigmar], the ground-floor bar hosts a bronze statue of Sigmar holding a Scythe, possibly a reference to the assiatance Sigmar recieved from Count Krugar at the Seige Of Middenheim.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">Upsatirs there are 2 Quad Rooms, 1 Bunkroom (Sleeps 8), and 1 Private Room; the staff, and service areas are in the basement.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0798%; height: 128px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\" colspan=\"3\"><strong>The Scythe &amp; Sigmar</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Lodgings &amp; Services</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Meals</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Drinks</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Bunkroom Bed: 8d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Porridge / Gruel: 4d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Standard Ale: 3d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Quad Room: 4/- each&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Stew and Bread: 1/-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Mead : 8d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Private Room: 10/-&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Bread, Fruit &amp; Cheese: 1/-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Spirits 1/4 Pint: 1/-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Roast Platter: 2/5d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Wine, Bottle, Good: 2/-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Clothes Service: 2d per item</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>The @JournalEntry[Temple of Sigmar] owns the land upon which the Inn sits, and takes a Church Tithe of 10% of the profit from the Inn, this money hlps ensure that the @JournalEntry[Priest's House], the @JournalEntry[Temple of Sigmar], and the @JournalEntry[Templemann Almshouse] are as well maintained as possible.</p>\n</section>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","img":"","_id":"d0W3yKJdqA3vFa6w"}
{"name":"Templemann Almshouse","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Next to the @JournalEntry[Temple of Sigmar] is Templemann Almshouse; a three-story dwelling. It os owned by the Temple of Sigmar, and is part funded by the donations to the Temple to provide subsidised housing for the poor of Halberst.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Ground Floor</p>\n<p>Small Kitchen with Dining Room; the kitchen provides an evening meal to the residents of the house for free.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>1st Floor</p>\n<p>Three single-room dwellings:</p>\n<p>1) &lt;TO SORT&gt;</p>\n<p>2) &lt;TO SORT&gt;</p>\n<p>3) &lt;TO SORT&gt;</p>\n<hr />\n<p>2nd Floor</p>\n<p>Two single room dwellings:</p>\n<p>1) &lt;TO SORT&gt;</p>\n<p>2) &lt;TO SORT&gt;</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Basement</p>\n<p>The house has a basement that sits behind a locked door, it is used for the storage of food stuff for the house residents, it has a small well opening, just big enough to lower a small bucket down.&nbsp; There are several cases of cheapish wine, that is mixed with the water for drinking.</p>","_id":"dEYHGdXvryHePLYM"}
{"name":"Threeways","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>At the junction of @JournalEntry[Upper Gottheim Road], @JournalEntry[Karstadt Road] and @JournalEntry[Baker's Row] is, perhaps the busiest area of Halberst, the Threeways.</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;@JournalEntry[Radecker's Yard] sits on the South-West of this junction, a collection of small shacks, low-traders, and a long building with several small workshops.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Because of its role as the main junction of the town's trafiic there is usually one or two members of the @JournalEntry[Halberst Garrison] on duty here, though when the weather is bad they can more often be found in the @JournalEntry[Two Soldiers Inn].</p>","_id":"dEi1hcwZ0M2IxlEM"}
{"name":"Lower Gottheim Road","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Gottheim Road is the Southerly road into and out of Halberst, it passes through the @JournalEntry[South Gate], and joins the @JournalEntry[Karstadt Road] and @JournalEntry[Baker's Row] at @JournalEntry[Threeways].</p>","_id":"dRC70veafGE9sC1U"}
{"name":"Drunken Rat Tavern","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pxh26pbtbf","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/06: Taverns & Inns","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><strong>Sign: </strong>A Frothing Tankard of Ale, with a Rat poking out.</p>\n<p><strong>Proprietor:</strong> @Actor[Rafton \"Ratty\" Tunnelberry]</p>\n<p><strong>Staff:</strong> &lt;To Sort&gt;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Drunken Rat (known locally as Ratty's Rat) has a small crowded bar, with room for roughly 35 people, and a bustling kitchen that serves good pies, savoury and sweet, all cooked in specially made pans that ensure they are just the right size as a stand alone meal.&nbsp; The proprietor is Rafton \"Ratty\" Tunnellberry.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0798%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%; text-align: center;\">Food and Drink</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">Cost</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">Ale, Pint</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">3d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">Mead, Pint</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">6d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">Spirits, shot</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">4d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">Wine, Bottle, 6 Goblets</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">2/8d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">Ale Pie: Beef, Onion &amp; Mushrrom in Ale Gray with Herbs.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">10d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">Guardsman's Pie: Gammon, Onion, Potato, Cheese, with Sage and WIld Garlic.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">1/-d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">Riverman's Pie: Fish, Onion, Celery &amp; Potato in a butter-based sauce.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">9d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">Clerk's Pie: Pork, Caramelised Onion, Mushrooms, and a fortified wine sauce.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">1/6d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">Rhubarb Pie: Rhubarb, Honey &amp; Ginger. with Sugar Glazed Crust</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">12d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">Apple Pie: Apples, Cinnamon, Raisins, and a sweet, creamy cheese.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">1/-d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 82.8971%;\">Estalian Pie:&nbsp; Almagoran Orange, Almonds, Nutmeg, Almagorn Brandy</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3288%; text-align: center;\">1/10d</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"eKb71QM28ioQSQqM"}
{"name":"Estimable Guild of Craftsmen","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":null,"_id":"eTwnVBlboCUbIz6p"}
{"name":"House Zohrnkreiger","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dqjx1ld0k6u","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/02: Noble & Trade Houses","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Sir @Actor[Rutgar Zohrnkreiger] is one of @Actor[Graf Steirlich von Bruner]'s longest serving and most trusted retainers.&nbsp; Indeed his family has served the von Bruners for almost 250 years.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Rutgar is Knight-Commander of the 1st Grauwerk Fusiliers, the Graf's personal guard, stationed at @JournalEntry[Steirlich Manor].&nbsp; House Zohrnkreiger holds lands around Duderfurt and once had a Town-House in Leche, but as the @JournalEntry[Leche Marshes] spread and made the Leche Docks less and less viable they established a new Town-House at Halberst.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>The house is centrally situated on Guild Street, there are 2 floors, and attic space for for the servants, as well as a basement used for provisions, with a small well shaft.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<p>The Lady @Actor[Alliane Zohrnkreiger] resides in Halberst, with her young, twin daughters, Camilla and Helena, and their Governess @Actor[Piperella Mazarin].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The houshold staff includes: Chamberlain @Actor[Hunold Kammermann], Cook @Actor[Annabella \"Bel\" Appleblossom], Guard Captain @Actor[Eloise Adelhof] assisted by 3 Guards, and House Clerk @Actor[Sezina Hoffron], as well as 5 other various household servants.</p>","_id":"etwkJaUwzY7wpOEN"}
{"name":"Trader's Row #1&2","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>&lt;BLANK&gt;</p>","_id":"fHVsMr7q9McrEJBC"}
{"name":"Stump House","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A two-storey building.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&lt;BLANK&gt;</p>","_id":"fJUM9QymVjwmqYNc"}
{"name":"South Gate","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The South Gate sits on the Gotheim Road and is one of two fortified gates into Halberst.&nbsp; The Gate is manned throughout the day, by a Watch Sergeant, and 3 Guards during the day; and by 2 Guards at night when the gate is closed.</p>","_id":"fPj9qsmAvdhUWHwX"}
{"name":"Noble Guild of Hostellers","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":null,"_id":"fZq3ZmxkpYarHiYk"}
{"name":"Burghermeister's Hall","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Guild Street heads South off of the @JournalEntry[Karstadt Road] and rises slightly up towards the @JournalEntry[Guilder's Market] which sits in front of the impressive @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall], the administartive centre of Halberst and the seat of Reeve @Actor[Constanza Landervogt].&nbsp; This street is better maintained than most in Halberst, and is also better patrolled by the @JournalEntry[Halberst Garrison].</p>","_id":"gItZPZU2CNr1ohiz"}
{"name":"House Hoflieger","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dqjx1ld0k6u","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/02: Noble & Trade Houses","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Recipients of an Hereditary Noble Charter just over 150 years ago House Hoflieger has used Halberst as its urban base of operations for all of its existence.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The House alos holds extensive farming lands at both Niemberg and Barsingdorf, and has a working Silver Mine roughly 15 miles from Halberst, and Hunting Lodge just a mile or two from the mine.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Actor[Sir Markhus Hoflieger] is the current head of the House and splits his time between Halberst (Winter) and his Hunting Lodge (Summer).&nbsp; His eldest son, by his first wife, currently also resides in Halberst.&nbsp; Sir Markhus worries that @Actor[Matthias Hoflieger]{Matthias} is too enamoured of the pleasures that wealth can bring.&nbsp; While he himslef loves to hunt in the Summer he has earned that right by 30 years of hard work and service to the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Karstadt]; Matthias on the other hand has spent most of his 24 years enjoying the privileges his father's hard work earned, while doing nothing of substance.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>His second wife, the Lady @JournalEntry[Katerlinda Hoflieger] prefers the more urbane life of Karstadt, staying the family's Town House there, and raising their children, Leonore (12) and Hanno (14).&nbsp; Hanno seems likely to enter the Knights of Sigmar, while Leonore seems well suited to the life of a noble lady.</p>","_id":"gfzFijxcCAVQF4ZG"}
{"name":"Upper Gottheim Road","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Gottheim Road is the Southerly road into and out of Halberst, it passes through the @JournalEntry[South Gate], and joins the @JournalEntry[Karstadt Road] and @JournalEntry[Baker's Row] at @JournalEntry[Threeways].</p>","_id":"guK6nuZ5YY2iT4sr"}
{"name":"House Unternehmer","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dqjx1ld0k6u","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/02: Noble & Trade Houses","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Based in @JournalEntry[Karstadt] House Unternehmer has extensive farm holdings around that town, and used to ship grain overland to Halberst and then into the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Grauwerk], they now ship it overland to @JournalEntry[Hagerdorf] down the @JournalEntry[Hagercryb Canal], through @JournalEntry[Ubersreik] and then on to Halberst.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>House Unternehmer is in the process of approaching @Actor[Graf Steirlich von Bruner] to seek a warrant to develop a Grain Warehouse and Dry Goods Dock at @JournalEntry[Hagerdorf].&nbsp; The Graf sees the value in this but is loathe to further reduce the fortunes of Halberst, and is keen to see that Halberst can develop other income streams before granting such permission.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>House Unternehmer does not have the political or monetary capital to circumvent the Graf in this endeavour, but under the leadership of the tenacious and calculating @Actor[Lenora Unternehmer] it is determined to have its way.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Without being aware of the wider implications of doing so @Actor[Fredric Hausmann], a retainer of the House, has started - via several layers of intermediaries - negotiations with @JournalEntry[The Sons of the Marsh] to raid the Halberst Warehouse and burn it down.</p>\n</section>","_id":"hZ6UT7HvSFnhiUqi"}
{"name":"Halberst Engravers & Silversmiths","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Halberst Engravers &amp; Silversmiths</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>At the end of the lane is a small one room cottage, that belong to @Actor[Balagrom Hargonsson], Halberst's resident engraver, and silversmith.&nbsp; Balagrom specialises in fine jewellery, brooches, and in the engraving of precious metals.&nbsp; Work arrives to him rarely, but somehow he manages to keep on paying his dues when the Reeve calls for his rent and taxes.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Balagrim is one of the \"@JournalEntry[12 Daggers]\", and supplements his legitimate income with minting fake silver coins, made with \"clippings\" from the coins taken over the bar at the @JournalEntry[Twelve Daggers Tavern].</p>\n</section>","_id":"iB02ufKohV2NmJ3p"}
{"name":"House Radecker","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_dqjx1ld0k6u","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/02: Noble & Trade Houses","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A minor trade house with a Contry Estate at Blitzhohe on the neighbouring Duchy of Haalstein, the house had some small trade interest in Halberst but withdrew from Halberst and consolidated their position in Blitzhohe; retaining the properties in Halberst purely to generate income from rent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Currently House Radecker is happy for the Halberst @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall] to accept the Rent payments, take a small levy, and pay the rest to their representative on his 6 monthly visits.</p>","_id":"iULukhrWkKcuEv3M"}
{"name":"Two Soldiers Inn","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pxh26pbtbf","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/06: Taverns & Inns","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><strong>Sign: </strong>A Two Soldiers standing back to back, one in the colours of the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Karstadt] and the second in the colours of the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Grauwerk]</p>\n<p><strong>Proprietor:</strong> @Actor[Hans-Gruber Fahnrich]</p>\n<p><strong>Staff:</strong> &lt;TO SORT&gt;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Where @JornalEntry[Coachman's Corner] sits on the @JornalEntry[Karstadt Road] the Two Soldiers Inn sits opposite the @JournalEntry[Halberst Garrison].&nbsp; The Inn is part-owned by the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Karstadt].&nbsp; The 6 Single Rooms are only available to Garrison Officers of the rank of Sergeant or higher.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>However, the subsidised food and drink prices are abailable to all, this ensures that the Inn maintains a very healthy trade, and makes the other Inns and Taverns in Halberst have to work much harder to maintain profitability, a situation the @JournalEntry[Noble Guild of Hostellers] has long complained about.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0798%; height: 128px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\" colspan=\"3\"><strong>The Two Soldiers</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Lodgings &amp; Services</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Meals</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Drinks</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">Single Room:&nbsp; 6d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Porridge / Gruel: 4d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Standard Ale: 3d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Bread, Fruit &amp; Cheese: 1/-</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Spirits 1/4 Pint: 1/-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">Roast Platter: 2/5d</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Wine, Bottle, Cheap: 1/3d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">Small Beer: 1d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 31.3178%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 36.0641%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.6892%; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","img":"","_id":"iUmBVi2WaArXda8H"}
{"name":"Hagerdorf","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y3t0m7yb3h","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/10: Connected Background Material","color":"#000000"}},"content":null,"_id":"ihl1NOOEC2zP96dM"}
{"name":"Krugelmann's Folly Hostel","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.b4SuHTvatE5uxklp"},"gm-notes":{"notes":null},"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Hans-Sebastian Kruglemann is famous in Halberst, despite being dead for almost 300 years. 270 years ago Kruglemann purchased, at great expense, a plot of land on @JournalEntry[Karstadt Road] from the Karstadt Family, and proceeded to build a \"luxury hostel\".&nbsp; At the time Halberst was little more than a village, with no walls, an intermittent Coach service, and very little in local industry and commerce beyond the subsistence level.&nbsp;&nbsp;Almost immediately became known as Krugelmann's Folly, and the name has stick ever since.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>However, as Halberst grew, and as the @JournalEntry[Leche Marshes] encroached upon the Leche Docks, forcing the Halberst Docks to expand, his vision seemed less foolish.&nbsp; The three-sotrey building he built has been renovated, but is still essentially the Hostel he built.&nbsp; The ground-floor is a Kitchen and a private dining room and bar; the second floor has just 3 Private Rooms, including one Stateroom; and the third-floor contains garret units for the staff.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Two of the rooms, including the Stateroom are, effectively, permanently occupied by long-term residents.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Stateroom: The von Bruner Suite</strong></p>\n<p>Christophe Schumacher, the famous Nuln playwright, has been ensconced in the Stateroom for almost 2 years; he has been diligently crafting his latest play, a morality play about an errant Doctor who makes a foolish bargain with the Ruinous Powers.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Room 1: The von Rothschmeid Suite</strong></p>\n<p>Anneka von Frischler von Elnel, a member of the minor nobility from the&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: rgba(53, 0, 121, 0.05);\">@JournalEntry[Duchy of Graustadt]</span>, seeking to procure contracts with Craftsmen of merit.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Lady Anneka von Frischler von Elnel is a cover for @Actor[Anneka Frischler], the Graf's Sheriff of @Item[Graf's Warrant]{Warrants} is in town, she is inspecting all such Warrants in and around Halberst.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Roll: Lore: Reikland +0 to discover:</p>\n<p>1SL: Elnel is party of the .</p>\n<p>2SL: It would be far easier to seek such contracts in Graustadt, just 10 or so miles away.</p>\n<p>3SL: There is no easily navigable route from Halberst to Elnel, and the routes that do exist wuld incur Tax Levies at either Aschaffen, or Ubersreik.</p>\n<p>4SL: You are sure the Leige-Lords of Elnel would be allied to the Jungfreuds.</p>\n<p>5SL: The actual Leige-Lords of Elnel is a minor branch of the House Jungfreud, the Karlfreuds.</p>\n</section>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Room 2: The von Weidner Suite</strong></p>\n<p>Currently vacant.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Staff</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Housekeeper: @Actor[Amala Weinstapft].</p>\n<p>Cook: @Actor[Verbena Kochfeuer]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","img":"","_id":"j4Iyv9KiKVTbGfiK"}
{"name":"3rd Company, 1st Karstadt Infantry","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The 3rd Company of the 1st Karstadt Infantry, known as The Bloody Feathers, is cuurently stationed at Halberst as the Town Garrison.&nbsp; &nbsp;They have been stationed at Halberst for a year and a half, and had been expecting to be redeployed a few months ago.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The 3rd Company tabbard is Three Upright White Feathers, with the tips bent over, and redened with blood, bound together with a Scroll bearing the Words \" I Karstadt, III\".</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Bloody Feathers is commanded by Guard Captain @Actor[Erika Jagermann], she is assisted by 4 Sergeants, one for each Platoon.&nbsp; Each Platoon consists of a Sergeant and 8 Guards.&nbsp; Currently 3rd Platoon only has 5 Guards.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>There are also two other Officers assisting with the Garrison, Quartermaster @Actor[Adelard \"Ade\" Billiter] and Surgeon-Sergeant @Actor[Mekel Leibarst].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<p>1st Platoon</p>\n<p>Sgt @Actor[Guard Sgt]{Andris Trabant}, Guards:&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<p>2nd Platoon</p>\n<p>Sgt @Actor[Guard Sgt]{Sepp Teuber}, Guards:</p>\n<hr />\n<p>3rd Platoon</p>\n<p>Sgt @Actor[Guard Sgt]{Jorn Hoefer}, Guards:</p>\n<hr />\n<p>4th Platoon</p>\n<p>Sgt @Actor[Guard Sgt]{Talima Becker}, Guards:</p>\n<hr />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"jbWj6vabNpNgHPE9"}
{"name":"Halberst Garrison","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.aKr3WnBEiF4d0qZc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Sitting on @JournalEntry[Coachman's Corner] opposite the @JournalEntry[Two Soldiers Inn] is the Halberst Garrison.&nbsp; The building is three-storeys above ground, and has a basement.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The @JournalEntry[3rd Company, 1st Karstadt Infantry], \"The Bloody Feathers\" are currently stationed in Halberst, and have been for the last year and a half.&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Ground Floor</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Office of Guard Captain:</strong> The administrative office for Guard Captain @Actor[Erika Jagermann].</p>\n<p><strong>Sergeants' Office:</strong> Smaller office shared by the 4 Sergeants, @Actor[Andris Trabant], Galisa Witmann, Tomas Shaumer, and Goran Traschel.</p>\n<p><strong>Assembly &amp; Briefing Room:</strong> The majority of the ground floor is an assembly area, also used for mass breifings.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">First Floor</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong> Kitchen &amp; Mess Hall:</strong> Long Mess tables with seating for 20 or so people.&nbsp; Quartermaster @Actor[Adelard \"Ade\" Billiter] runs the mess-hall like a military campaign, he is also responsible for buying and maintaining the Garrison's non-military supplies.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Captain's Quarters:</strong> A small room just large enough for a bed, a wardrobe, a small writing desk, and a foot locker.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Second Floor</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Guards' Bunk Room:</strong> A series of Double-Bunks, each fitted with an \"foot locker\", there are enough beds for 12 Guardsmen.&nbsp; There is a rudimentary \"screen\" separating 4 of the bunks, made with a couple of sheets hanging over a rope.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Basement</span></strong></p>\n<p>The bassement contains storage space for dried goods, and a salt-box contain salted meats, and a dozen or so sacks of vegetables and hard fruits.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In one corner there is also a small well-shaft, just large enough to take a bucket, it drops down to a small underground stream that feeds in to the river.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>There is also a secret second level of basement, smaller than the first level, that houses further dried goods.&nbsp; Only the Guard Captain and Quartermaster know how to access it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Concealed Lock:</strong> <em>Extremely Hard -40 to Spot</em>. <em>Extremely Hard -40 to Pick</em>.</p>\n</section>\n<p>.</p>","img":"","_id":"k6A14Yfwnqkb8W6M"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000","name":"07: Dwellings","children":["ubViiao8NyamfM4n","UbsYANKvKCd4npxF","71aDgtRSkt96v3Ex","Jf26PJvuhEofQfQ6","FTXvQ7thlFquAAot","vm7dDIXtYJUwboyl","Hb8rTIG4cOk90EJe","5mav4opOu0HUfxck","j4Iyv9KiKVTbGfiK","LFhBcz7F4roDd1bi","9IqpLiYjbjJde3Gm","rS0f2FRwDvqpoekp","x8NznsNEaRFASO7W","xll79UZm4g8GRR7e","04Damtjb5Jkm2v8K","NHXN0fQHgmtsmc5u","HoVT3H0wr2Rbt8O3","KnYGQA3dHcDrr893","ZdBaSnABgMMY5bn7","fJUM9QymVjwmqYNc","SG1Pm49RnpIGnwHE","dEYHGdXvryHePLYM","QK0Q9ZdZliCbplaC","fHVsMr7q9McrEJBC","ZKyD4kpw5oqQZN22"],"folderPath":["temp_syvf2bs7n7"]}},"content":"","_id":"kAdJttnYs3sOi7MZ"}
{"name":"Hardtstein's Hardware","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>@Actor[Thyrus Hardtstein]'s grandfather came to Halberst to establish a hardware business, he succeeded, and passed it on to his son, who very nearly lost the business due to his lack of business accumen.&nbsp; In order to save the family business Thyrus was forced to seek investment from an external party.&nbsp; Having done so, and re-established his lines of credit, he was able to continue trading.&nbsp; The Store sells pots and pans, household goods, blankets, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Because of the wide variety of goods Hardtstein's sells it is one of the larger building in Halberst.&nbsp; The ground floor at the front is the shop, the upper floor is the Hardtstein family home; to the rear of the shop is a split-level warehouse, there is a loading door to the rear of the warehouse.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Street Gossip: 1</p>\n<p>\"Hardtstein's was close to bankruptcy just a year or two ago, Thyrus' father was a bad gambler\"</p>\n</section>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Street Gossip: 2</p>\n<p>\"Young Thyrus has done a fantastic job of saving the family business; his mother must be very proud.\"&nbsp;</p>\n</section>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Thyrus was forced to sell part of the business to @JournalEntry[House Landervogt], in fact they now own a controlling share, and take 5/8ths of the profit.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Unbeknown to Thyrus it was House Landervogt that called in his Father's debt, causing the business to flounder, and lose lines of credit in the first place.</p>\n</section>","_id":"kVFE18DJGFtBdceP"}
{"name":"Halberst Granary","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Granary is widely considered one of the most important buildings in Halberst. As such it is constantly guarded by at least one @JournalEntry[Halberst Garrison] soldier.&nbsp; The Granary is managed by @Actor[Haletha Amtskeller] hired personally by Graf Stierlich von Bruner's Chamberlain - @Actor[Oskar Kammermann]; she is a Member (IGS) of the @JournalEntry[Learned Guild of Administrators &amp; Excisemen].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Granary is constantly in use as new grain comes in, and older grain is rotated out and sold to the inhabitants and traders of Halberst.&nbsp; The Granary is used, at a price, by @Actor[Casimir Salzman] a Salt Merchant and Member (IGS) of the @JournalEntry[Honourable Fellowship of Merchants &amp; Traders] to store his Salt in a secure and dry building.</p>","_id":"kkMonqvX9sqUn9M1"}
{"name":"Steinhauers","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Stonemason @Actor[Dietrich Steinhauers].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Stone brought into town from Quarry North of Barsingdorf.</p>","_id":"lLUiUCY5wPimVrFs"}
{"name":"Graf's Warrant","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A Graf's Warrant is a wooden plaque. bearing a carved and painted version of the seal of @Actor[Graf Steirlich von Bruner], signifying that the Trader, Merrchant or Craftsman has the distinguished honour of having supplied goods and services to the Graf's Household.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Businesses who have been granted a Garf's Warrant are able to increase thier prices, and will likely see increased patronage from the well-to-do of the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Karstadt] and @JournalEntry[Duchy of Grauwerk], and even @JournalEntry[Ubersreik] and beyond.</p>","_id":"mPbhaAtrTt5ybhqN"}
{"name":"Cooper's Lane","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>On @JournalEntry[Trader's Row] is small, dead-end, lane called Cooper's Lane.&nbsp; The primary building here is, even after 30 years of being repurposed, known as @JournalEntry[The Old Coach House].&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>","_id":"ost0o8H9HtCGesi7"}
{"name":"Haffner's Pottery","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>@Actor[Patrycja Haffner] is Halberst's potter, she is assisted by her young son @Actor[Tristram Haffner]{Tristram}.&nbsp; Her husband @Actor[Krugar Haffner]{Krugar} has a small, flat-boat, that he plies up and down the Teufal, gatherinf Clay, and Cutting Peat from the finges of the @JournalEntry[Leche Marshes].&nbsp; Her elder son @Actor[Matz Haffner] is a Kitchen Porter at the @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall].</p>","_id":"pBFFdZZ0A5WA5XIq"}
{"name":"The Stump","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A raised rock outcropping that has proven more than a match for any attempts made to level it, The Stump sits at the top of @JournalEntry[Upper Dock Street], and is the main featue of @JornalEntry[Threeways].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Thre building sit upon The Stump, the @JournalEntry[River Warden's] Office, a two-storey dwelling, currently occupied by the&nbsp; Malzmunn family, and @JournalEntry[Kahnsmann's Portage Services].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"pDQzHCH4YmqG4m6g"}
{"name":"The Old Coach House","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A little over 30 years ago this building was the Coach House, but as the local Coach Routes were bought up by the large Coaching Lines, it fell out of use.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The workshop however could quite easily be used for another prupose, the making of barrels.&nbsp; Accordingly, it was repurposed and a cooper was bought in from Leche.&nbsp; @Actor[Mikel Fassbender] had only recently completed his apprenticeship at Leche when we was offered his own Coopery in Halberst.&nbsp; For the last 30 years he has plied his trade in Halberst, married, and has two children.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As he was bought to Halberst by the Graf's Chamberlain it was inevitable that he would be awarded a @JournalEntry[Graf's Warrant], and has held it for the last 12 years.</p>","img":"","_id":"qEMlhpu1UPA0D8zT"}
{"name":"Bart's Smithy","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>With a wooden sign depicting an Anvil, a Hammer, and a Sword it easy to identify Bartenhauer's as the Halberst Weaponsmith, known locally as \"Bart's Smithy\".&nbsp; A two-storey building with large double doors on the street front where the workshop is located, and external stairs on the side leading up to the home above.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Heinz Bartenhauer is long-dead, having passed away almost 70 years ago, but the building still carries his name, though it is doubtful anyone now alive remembers him.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The current occupier of Bart's Smithy is @Actor[Chrysta Dengler] a master-smith who trained among the forges at @JournalEntry[Ubersreik], she is particulalry adept at making Axes.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"qfzHLWX7638Jq50c"}
{"name":"Temple of Sigmar","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_785h5s8h1e9","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/08: Religion","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Standing proudly in the centre of Temple Street, and dominating the street with its gothic facade is the Temple of Sigmar.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>To the right of he building is a section of scaffold, belying the fact that the Temple, like so much of the officialdom of Halberst, is in a state of slight disrepair.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Father @Actor[Luther Probst] is the head of the Temple, and is assisted by Brother @Actor[Klaus Kruden], and the recently appointed Novice @Actor[Dekmar Hirsch]</p>","img":"","_id":"qnCppuDWpk3Me2dV"}
{"name":"West Gate","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Sitting across the @JournalEntry[Karstadt Road] is the West Gate is dominated by the City Gate, and the adjacent Watch House.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"rAOVblaTMPWvVELy"}
{"name":"Lenkster's Row #1","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>&lt;BLANK&gt;</p>","_id":"rS0f2FRwDvqpoekp"}
{"name":"12 Daggers","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Twelve Daggers Inn has been host to the \"12 Daggers\" since the day it opened its doors for the first time almost 170 years ago.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As Halberst's fortunes started to grow, and commerce began to increase a niche market was seen to be emerging - Organised Crime.&nbsp; Thus, 12 entrepenurial residents of Halberst pooled their resources, and petitioned the Reeve to purcahse some land, and build a tavern.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The tavern was built to access a natural cave in the rocky rise that the @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall] sits on, and in fact it secretly connects with the Cellars of the Hall.&nbsp; This gives the 12 Daggers access to the corridors of power, and they have used this access to further their aims.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>There are not always 12 Daggers, thought the Daggers themselves like to perpetuate the myth that there are; occassionally&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Current Members, and their positions:</p>\n<p>Director: @Actor[Abighild Kretschner]</p>\n<p>Convener: @Actor[Siegmund \"Ziggy\" Kuppler]</p>\n<p>Enforcer: @Actor[Vargaz Untroksson]</p>\n<p>Treasurer: @Actor[Karsten Stadler]</p>\n<p>Fence: @Actor[Irina Haake], small trinkets.</p>\n<p>Fence: @Actor[Sebastian \"Seb\" Steinschneider], larger gems, precious metals.</p>\n<p>Forger: @Actor[Balagrom Hargonsson]</p>\n<p>Intelligence: @Actor[Edegar Reiss], specifically goods held within dock warehouses.</p>\n<p>Intelligence: @Actor[Solange Aubergiere], specifically, coaching information.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Intelligence: @Actor[Wilhelm Beschlager].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"sCACRUVEc69x6cG0"}
