{"name":"Lenkster's Row","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>As the North end of lenkster's Court narrows again, it becomes Lenkster's Row, containing a few houses and @JournalEntry[Dankov Lenkster's Shack].&nbsp; Below the rise on which the @JournalEntry[Wandering Bretonian Inn] sits the bank between the two is a prime location for wild herbs, especially wild garlic, sage, and thyme.</p>","_id":"tmOumnY0rgh6YSUL"}
{"name":"Wandering Bretonian Bathhouse","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pxh26pbtbf","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/06: Taverns & Inns","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Standing to the side of the @JournalEntry[Wandering Bretonian Inn] is the bathhouse and laundry.&nbsp; Managed in conjuction with the Inn, it is the only Bathhouse in Halberst, and so is a very lucrative business.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Tha bathhouse and laundry is staffed by @Actor[Hanna Kammerling]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Hot Bath: 6d</p>\n<p>Laundry Service: 2d per item, overnight service.</p>","img":"","_id":"tnUMa0adTLfei8Uc"}
{"name":"Counting-House","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A fully stone-built building, with a paved area out front.&nbsp; A Guard stands either side of the door at all times, and there are two more guards inside.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Counting House bears all the signs of being a relativel new building, the windows are narrow and barred, the door is oaken and iron-bound.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>During a visit to Halberst 5 or so years ago @Actor[Graf Stierlich von Bruner]'s Chamberlain decided that the small Counting Room in the @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall] was neither large enough, nor secure enough, for the volume of coin that flows through Halberst.&nbsp; He commissioned a new Counting House, and secured land for it to the rear of @JournalEntry[Temple Street #3].&nbsp; The following Summer a crew of stonemasons and labourers arrived via river from Karstadt, and proceded to construct the Counting House.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>The Counting House takes up all of the lower floor, but the coin is actually kept in a secure basement area, with iron-bound walls and doors.&nbsp; The upper floor is a bunkhouse for the six Coin-Guards that live, eat and sleep here.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Meals are bought in from the @JournalEntry[Scythe &amp; Sigmar Inn].&nbsp; At the start of the business day two Coin-Guard walk to the Berghermeister's Hall and escort the @Actor[Klara Geldenrektor]{Reeve's Treasurer} to the Counting House; at the end of the day two more escort her back to either the Burghermeister's Hall, ot her residence @JournalEntry[Karstadt Road #3].</p>\n</section>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"tvdVchGIhADj0N5E"}
{"name":"Baker's Row #1 & 2","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Nestled between @JournalEntry[Brotbacker's Bakery] and @JournalEntry[Kellner's Boarding House] are two joined dwellings, both are two-storey single-room houses.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1) &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>\n<p>2) &lt;BLANK&gt;</p>","_id":"ubViiao8NyamfM4n"}
{"name":"The Sons of the Marsh","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y3t0m7yb3h","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/10: Connected Background Material","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>150 years ago the town of @JournalEntry[Aschaffen] was included in a grant of a Patent Of Nobility by Magnus The Pious, to the newly formed House Aschaffenberg.&nbsp; Prior to that it had been included in the domain of a minor branch of House Walfen,&nbsp; the Walfen-Rausch family.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>With the loss of their lands the family effectively became peasants, although the scions of the main Walfen bloodline continued on as leaders of the other House Holdings, but were in effect puppets of the Emperor.&nbsp; This situation continues to the modern day, with Viktor von Walfen the Archduke of the Upper Teufel technically being the rightful ruler of Ubersreik and the Duchy of Ubersreik; but with him being a \"guest\" of The Emperor at an undisclosed location he has no power at all.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>However, the remnants of the Walfen-Rausch family have long harboured the desire to be returned to their rightful lands.&nbsp; In the early days of their disnfranchisement the family sought to use official channels and processes to try and regain their position, however it soon became apparent that no one was willing to consider reversing the grant made by Magnus The Pious.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Accordingly the last 2 generations of the family have sought to undermine the Aschaffenbergs by other means.&nbsp; For many years Kaleb Walfen established a smuggling network to financially undermine the Aschaffenberg income streams; his son Sigric, however has used that network to take more direct action against Aschaffenberg interests.&nbsp; He has pulled together the small network of smuggler his late father had established and formed them into a Wrecker Crew based out of the @JournalEntry[Leche Marshes].&nbsp; He leads the wreckers as @Actor[Steffan Verschwenderisch], and has a reputation for brutality and ruthless determination.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Meanwhile his sister, Ingrun, under the name of @Actor[Imogen Ohrstenbach] has infiltrated the Aschaffen docks and has established herself as a Shipping Agent.&nbsp; She has used her position to pass information to @Actor[Steffan Verschwenderisch] that enables him to carefully target specific shipments in and out of Aschaffen; notably he has been targeting shipments of timber.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Deep in the @JournalEntry[Leche Marshes] the Sons of the Marsh are building a small fleet of boats; boats they will use to bring Ashaffenberg commercial interests on the river to a standstill.&nbsp; The Sons need about another three months to complete the fleet, and then maybe a further month or two to recruit and train crews.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Actor[Steffan Verschwenderisch]{Sigric} has some of his trusted lieutenants travelling the length of&nbsp; @JournalEntry[The Teufel] from @JournalEntry[Ubersreik] to @JournalEntry[Gr&uuml;nburg] trying to recruit crews for their boats.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>","_id":"ujA41H67z3u7Rc2o"}
{"name":"South Gate Watch-House","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>On the upper floor of the @JournalEntry[Docker's Rise Market] is the South Gate Watch-House.&nbsp; Offering easy access to @JournalEntry[South Gate] and @JournalEntry[Lower Gottheim Road], and shelter to the Watchmen who stand guard.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The room is little more than a table with 4 chairs, a fireplace with a small pot for making Possets (warmed milk curdled with ale or wine) and Small Beer (watered down ale, heated), to keep the Watchmen warm.&nbsp; The room also has a double bunk-bed.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>","_id":"uz1j2Qpwek2sO3E3"}
{"name":"Porter's Wynd","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>To the East of the @JournalEntry[Burghermeister's Hall] is Porter's Wynd (a local dialect word meaning \"lane\"), it gives access to the @JournalEntry[Porter's Kitchen] at the rear of the Hall, and to the @JournalEntry[Reeve's House]</p>","_id":"v2tYdCNPiSO9hHEm"}
{"name":"Steinschneider's","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>@Actor[Sebastian \"Seb\" Steinschneider] is a master jeweller, he trained for 7 years under the tutelage of the renowned Jeweller Abner Achatshleifer of @JournalEntry[Kemperbad].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sebastian is proud to hold a @JournalEntry[Graf's Warrant], and is not only a Member (IGS) of the @JournalEntry[Estimable Guild of Craftsmen], but is also the Chairman of the guild.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sebastian specialises in the cutting and polishing of Amber, and a very rare gemstone, rumoured to be imported from Albion called Blauczahn.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sebastian is one of the @JournalEntry[12 Daggers]</p>\n</section>","img":"","_id":"vB5f62LjnyChqXKQ"}
{"name":"Religious Ranks","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_785h5s8h1e9","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/08: Religion","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Novitiate, Deacon, Aspirant</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Priest, Brother, Sister,&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Chaplain, Father, Mother Superior.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Abbot, Abbess, High Priest, High Priestess, Bishop.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Archbishop.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"vLAmP3ldzWVNxUBm"}
{"name":"Karstadt Road #3","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.b4SuHTvatE5uxklp"},"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>@Actor[Klara Geldenrektor]</p>","_id":"vm7dDIXtYJUwboyl"}
{"name":"Irina Haake's Trinkets","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A small market stall on the front porch of the @JournalEntry[Twelve Daggers Tavern] is @Actor[Irina Haake]'s Trinket Stall.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Selling small trinkets of varying worth, and authenticity Irina makes just enough to get by and pay her stall rent to @Actor[Siegmund Kuppler].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Irina is a member of the @JournalEntry[12 Daggers] and her stall is a front used to move small, semi-precious and precious items that they have \"acquired\".&nbsp; Irina affects a Strigani accent, and looks the part, but she, like all The Daggers, local to the region around Halberst.</p>\n</section>","_id":"vmdfUILMvJA9PZX1"}
{"name":"Landervogt Warehouse","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Warehouse is currently owned by @JournalEntry[House Landervogt], and leased to Halberst for a percentage of the taxes that flow through the South Dock.&nbsp; The ground floor is used for heavy and larger goods; while the upper floor is used for lighter, smaller, and fragile goods, or goods that could be ruined in the event of a flood.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The ground floor also contains the Office of Master of the @JournalEntry[Esteemed Guild of Dockers &amp; Stevedores], which is used as the main tax office for all goods entering and leaving Halberst by river.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Constanza Landervogt has been very carefully rescheduling some of the tax-codes for various goods, to ensure that they enter the town via the South Docks, rather than the @JournalEntry[North Docks], so far this has gone unoticed, but is sure to be spotted eventually when @JournalEntry[House Unternehmer] starts to see significant drop in its revenues from the North Dock.</p>\n</section>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"voRINbkjbANvwzA3"}
{"name":"Fellhauer's Premium Leather Goods","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Fellhauer's Premium Leather Goods</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Actor[Rudi Fellhauer] has his leatherwork shop here, on the ground floor of an impressive stone building.&nbsp; He accepts comissions from the great and the good of Halberst and beyond, and has even had a few commissions from @Actor[Grav Steirlich von Bruner] himself, permitting him to display the @JournalEntry[Graf's Warrant] on his door, as a mark of quality.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Rudi specialises in Leather Scabbards, and Belts for weapon Scabbards; he is known for his intricate embossing, and decorative stud-work.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>The cost for any Leatherwork carried out by Rudi is double to quadruple that normally charged for such work; depending on the materials and finish selected by the client.</p>\n</section>","_id":"w0KjR7FJ2BsVZOm9"}
{"name":"Reeve's Lane","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Linking @JournalEntry[Guilder's Market] and @JournalEntry[Trader's Row] is Reeve's Lane, partially blocked by overgrwon shrubs and weeds the lane used to be used frequently by the former Reeve, Kasparus Landervogt, to visit his mistress on @JournalEntry[Trader's Row], but since his passing just over a year ago has become less well used.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The current Reeve, @Actor[Constanza Landervogt], the former Reeve's widow, has no interest in clearing the lane, preferring to see it become overgrown.</p>","_id":"w78YXhdvrP7rm4i4"}
{"name":"Barony of Bohrn","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_y3t0m7yb3h","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/10: Connected Background Material","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Barony of B&ouml;hrn is a Reikland Estate of the Vorbergland ruled by House B&ouml;hrn for over four centuries. Baroness Agetta holdscourt in the town of Siedlung and currently has six vassals: three with hereditary titles: Baron Markham of Siebbach, Countess Osterhild of Kaltenwald, and Baron Baltzer of Ettlindal, and three with non-hereditary titles, all of which were appointed by Agetta personally: Warden Fabian of Ort, Warden Luethold of Koff, and Castellan Fronika of Neumarkt. The three hereditary vassals have, in turn, a total of seven vassals of their own.</p>\n<p>The Baroness does not attend the Reikland Diet; instead she relies on her influential younger sister, Lector Agatha von B&ouml;hrn, to watch over it in her place. Agatha resides in Altdorf serving as a member of the Imperial Council of State and the Reikland Council, as well as tending to her duties as a Lector of Verena.</p>","_id":"w7A3rGhkuIWdWRBa"}
{"name":"Guilder's Market","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>There are three Market Stalls, and traditionally they are reserved for traders from the farms to the West of Halberst.&nbsp; These traders come into town the moment the Town Gates are opened, bringing their produce into town on hand carts.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>There are almost a dozen tennat-farmers to the West of Halberst, not all of them will bring produce to town every day, so the type of produce available can very from day to day.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Produce Available, depending on season.</p>\n<p>Beans (D), Peas (D), Cabbages (C), Onions, Turnips (C), Apples (C), Pears, Cherries, Eggs, Leeks, Parsnip (C), Oats.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>(D): can be dried to be used \"out of season\".</p>\n<p>(C): can be \"clamped\" to be used \"out of season\".</p>","_id":"wJdhP6MVfm8MRAjr"}
