{"name":"Lenkster's Shack","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_z9rp4yueeh","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/07: Dwellings","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>At the North end of @JournalEntry[Lenkster's Row] is a two-story dwelling in a state of significant disrepair, a set of wooded stairs, in better condition that the shack, leads up to @JournalEntry[Breton's Corner].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The shack belongs to @Actor[Dankov Lenkster], a drunkard and a fisherman.&nbsp; Rumours abound that Dankov is the last member of a once noble house, rumours he neither confirms nor denies, usually because he is too drunk to care.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Dankov's family, an up and coming Merchant House on the brink of being offered a Noble Warrant, once owned all of @JournalEntry[Lenkster's Row] and @JournalEntry[Lenkster's Court (East View)] and @JournalEntry[Lenkster's Court (West View)]; they also owned a river-side manor house 2 miles to the North of Halberst.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As the @JournalEntry[Leche Marshes] started to spread further South the Manor-House and its attendant lands fell into disrepair, and House Lenkster was put under increasing financial pressure every time the annual levy was due, forcing them to sell some of their property in Halberst.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Finally Dankov's mother sold the rest of the family's holdings on the proviso that Dankov could live in the house at the end of Lenkster Row rent, and tax free until he died.&nbsp; The then Reeve agreed.&nbsp; Dankov fell back to his forbears' original trade of fishing.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n</section>","img":"","_id":"xll79UZm4g8GRR7e"}
{"name":"Kahnsmann's Portage Services","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>A delapidated three-storey building, with a multi-level jetty leading down to the water, Kahnsmann's has been unoccupied for almost 2 years, until very recently that is.&nbsp; Six months ago the building was purchased by @Actor[Tobias Lutzenbruder], who has swiftly established an overland cargo transport business, and currently runs three teams of Horses and Wagons.</p>","_id":"yH69uOhVQ6WyM6xH"}
{"name":"West-Gate Watch House","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_45ug24i92fc","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/04: Organisations & Officialdom","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The West-Gate Watch House is a two-story building, the ground floor is a watch-station, and also has a rudimentary prison cell.&nbsp; The upper floor is a Guard's Common Room, and a Sergeant's Ready Room.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The West Gate is manned by a Sergeant and 4 Guards during the day, and by 4 guards rotating 2 on / 2 off during the evening when the gates are closed.</p>","_id":"yf6ypUbiaA3RT366"}
{"name":"Scherbart's Barber-Surgeon","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zskxgl70tbe","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/03: Merchants & Traders","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>@Actor[Adelina \"Lina\" Scherbart] is the resident Barber-Surgeon for Halberst, she has her shop on the ground floor of a building just inside the @JournalEntry[South Gate], next door to the @JournalEntry[Twelve Daggers Tavern].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Lina has been in business for over 10 years, and has a solid reputation among the inhabitants of Halberst.&nbsp; She retuned to Halberst from @JournalEntry[Nuln] to take over the family business when her father passed 12 years ago, and while the older, more traditional Halberstians were at first wary of a woman holding such a role, they soon came to trust her very effective skills.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0798%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 81.117%;\"><strong>Services</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.109%;\"><strong>Cost</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 81.117%;\">Haircut, Man:</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.109%;\">5d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 81.117%;\">Haircut, Woman:</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.109%;\">8d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 81.117%;\">Tooth Extraction:</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.109%;\">2/6d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 81.117%;\">Ear Piercing:</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.109%;\">1/6d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 81.117%;\">Dressing Minor Wound:</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.109%;\">6/10d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 81.117%;\">Dressing Major Wound:</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.109%;\">12/6d</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 81.117%;\">Setting Broken Bone:</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.109%;\">1GC&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 81.117%;\">Abortion (Surgical):</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.109%;\">10/-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 81.117%;\">Amputation: (Surgical), removal and tidying-up of critically damaged limb:</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18.109%;\">2GC 3/-</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Lina is professionally trained, and knows how to properly carry out the above services, whilst reducing the risks of infection, and bleeding-out etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>","_id":"ylhYvIQn6l8efa0t"}
{"name":"Hagercryb Canal","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"flags":{"gm-notes":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_y3t0m7yb3h","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/10: Connected Background Material","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>The Hagercryb canal runs from Siedlung in the @JournalEntry[Barony of Bohrn] to @JournalEntry[Ubersreik], it passes through Neumarkt, @JournalEntry[Hagerdorf], and @JournalEntry[Geissback].&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Still only a few decades old the canal has not yet managed to generate the volume of commercial traffic that it was hoped it would.&nbsp; This is in part because Night Berths are few and far between, and there is as yet only a minimal Road Warden presence.&nbsp; The Steam-Lock North of @JournalEntry[Dunkelbuche Woods] is the last Lock before Ubersreik and is also the last official Night Berth.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[House Unternehmer] is in negotiations with @Actor[Graf Steirlich von Bruner] to create a Night Berth and Dock facility at @JournalEntry[Hagerdorf]; which would server Karstadt and the North portion of the @JournalEntry[Duchy of Karstadt] while avoiding a further levy of taxes at Ubersreik.</p>","img":"","_id":"z8MOQDusZ1uR9GC7"}
{"_id":"Xk7C6pnI2MhgdBH8","name":"Artisan's Corner","permission":{"default":0,"Cu0IHETA1sncNnls":3},"folder":"","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3iwypo9lpov","path":"Halberst#/CF_SEP/01: Overview","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Close to the North Wall, where @JournalEntry[Kennel Lane] meets @JournalEntry[Beggar's Rise] you'll find Artisan's Corner; a few buildings that are home to some of the elite craftsmen of the town.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Here can be found @JournalEntry[Fellhauer's Premium Leather Goods], @JournalEntry[Flickschuster's Shoe Repairs], @JournalEntry[Krudener's Apothecarium], and @JournalEntry[Halberst Engravers &amp; Silversmiths].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Perched on a slight rise of land behind Krudener's, and accessed via a worn and rickety wooden staircase, is @JournalEntry[Steinschneider's], a single room, poorly maintained building.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","img":"worlds/uber-chron/images/Halberst/Hal_Artisan_Corner.png"}
